1
00:01:26,019 --> 00:01:30,589
FOUR? THEY'RE CRAZY.
I SHOULD JUST GET UP
AND WALK OUT RIGHT NOW.

2
00:01:30,591 --> 00:01:31,490
OKAY, CALM DOWN.

3
00:01:31,492 --> 00:01:33,725
HONESTLY, WE PUT
A SOLID OFFER
ON THE TABLE.

4
00:01:33,727 --> 00:01:35,727
MY CLIENTS ARE SELLING
FOR FOUR,

5
00:01:35,729 --> 00:01:37,896
LEAVING HALF A MILLION
IN EQUITY.

6
00:01:37,898 --> 00:01:39,264
NOW, THIS IS THE DEAL.

7
00:01:39,266 --> 00:01:40,099
NO. NO.

8
00:01:40,101 --> 00:01:42,968
RICHARD,
PLEASE SIT DOWN.

9
00:01:42,970 --> 00:01:45,871
[SILENT]

10
00:01:45,873 --> 00:01:47,906
[RICHARD SIGHS]

11
00:01:52,579 --> 00:01:54,179
I'LL SHOW THIS TO MY CLIENTS.

12
00:01:54,181 --> 00:01:58,383
DON'T KNOW IF IT'LL FLY,
BUT WE'LL SEE.

13
00:01:59,819 --> 00:02:02,020
HEY, HOW'S IT GOING
IN THERE? ANYTHING
I CAN DO?

14
00:02:02,022 --> 00:02:03,589
LISTEN. WHEN
BILL AND NORA LEAVE,

15
00:02:03,591 --> 00:02:06,158
I WANT YOU TO
POP YOUR HEAD INTO
THE CONFERENCE ROOM

16
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:08,293
AND I WANT YOU TO SAY
THESE EXACT WORDS--

17
00:02:08,295 --> 00:02:09,695
"YOUR CLIENTS ARE LEAVING."

18
00:02:09,697 --> 00:02:13,398
SURE. ANYTHING ELSE
I NEED TO KNOW?

19
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,234
NO, NOT YET.

20
00:02:15,236 --> 00:02:18,137
HMM.

21
00:02:18,139 --> 00:02:19,104
WELL?

22
00:02:19,106 --> 00:02:20,239
3.5 MILLION.

23
00:02:20,241 --> 00:02:22,774
WE ALREADY CAME DOWN
FROM FOUR.

24
00:02:22,776 --> 00:02:26,879
WE'LL ONLY BREAK EVEN IF WE
AGREE TO THREE AND A HALF.

25
00:02:26,881 --> 00:02:27,779
DO YOU TRUST ME?

26
00:02:27,781 --> 00:02:28,480
WE KNOW YOU'RE WORKING

27
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:32,050
AS HARD AS YOU CAN
TO CLOSE THIS DEAL,
BUT THAT RICHARD GUY

28
00:02:32,052 --> 00:02:33,118
IS TAKING
ADVANTAGE OF US.

29
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:36,655
I KNOW. THAT'S
WHY IF YOU TRUST ME,

30
00:02:36,657 --> 00:02:39,558
I WANT YOU TO DO EXACTLY
WHAT I'M ABOUT TO TELL YOU.

31
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,993
IN 10 MINUTES I NEED
FOR YOU TO GET UP,

32
00:02:40,995 --> 00:02:45,998
WALK OUT OF THIS OFFICE,
PAST THE CONFERENCE ROOM,
AND OUT THE DOOR.

33
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,002
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF NEGOTIATING.

34
00:02:50,004 --> 00:02:50,802
TRUST ME.

35
00:02:50,804 --> 00:02:54,206
HAVEN'T YOU EVER
DONE SOMETHING WITHOUT
KNOWING THE OUTCOME?

36
00:02:54,208 --> 00:02:57,009
WAIT 10 MINUTES
AND GO HOME.

37
00:02:57,011 --> 00:02:58,844
THE NEXT TIME
YOU'LL HEAR FROM ME

38
00:02:58,846 --> 00:03:01,013
WILL BE ME CALLING
TO CONGRATULATE YOU.

39
00:03:01,015 --> 00:03:02,247
<i>DO YOU UNDERSTAND NOW?</i>

40
00:03:02,249 --> 00:03:03,148
NOT REALLY.

41
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:07,920
BILL, LET'S JUST DO
WHAT SHE ASKS.

42
00:03:09,122 --> 00:03:12,291
'KAY. 10 MINUTES.

43
00:03:14,327 --> 00:03:15,827
LET ME CALL YOU BACK.

44
00:03:15,829 --> 00:03:16,562
WELL?

45
00:03:16,564 --> 00:03:19,898
DO WE HAVE A DEAL OR NOT?

46
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:22,734
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU
AND THIS PAPER?

47
00:03:22,736 --> 00:03:27,973
CAN'T YOU SPEAK?
WHAT DID THEY SAY?
DO WE HAVE A DEAL OR NOT?

48
00:03:29,742 --> 00:03:32,077
YOU'RE CRAZY!
NO, THEY'RE CRAZY!

49
00:03:32,079 --> 00:03:36,481
4.2 MILLION?
WHAT IS GOING ON HERE?

50
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:38,951
WE MADE A FAIR OFFER AND
THEY'RE GOING UP IN PRICE?

51
00:03:38,953 --> 00:03:42,087
THEY'RE TIRED OF
THIS BACK AND FORTH,
PUSH AND PULL.

52
00:03:42,089 --> 00:03:46,024
AND THEY SAID IF YOU DO NOT
AGREE TO IT IN 10 MINUTES,

53
00:03:46,026 --> 00:03:49,294
THE DEAL'S OFF THE TABLE.

54
00:03:49,296 --> 00:03:50,696
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

55
00:03:50,698 --> 00:03:53,632
3.7 MILLION
IS A LOT OF MONEY.

56
00:03:53,634 --> 00:03:57,202
<i>I MEAN, WHO'S GONNA</i>
<i>WALK AWAY FROM THAT?</i>

57
00:03:58,171 --> 00:04:00,072
YOUR CLIENTS?
THEY'RE LEAVING?

58
00:04:00,074 --> 00:04:03,075
THEY'RE WALKING OUT
OF THE BUILDING RIGHT NOW.

59
00:04:03,077 --> 00:04:04,076
WELL, I GUESS THAT MEANS
THE DEAL'S OFF.

60
00:04:04,078 --> 00:04:08,780
WHAT? AFTER ALL THE TIME
AND WORK I PUT INTO THIS?

61
00:04:08,782 --> 00:04:09,314
GO. GO GET THEM.

62
00:04:09,316 --> 00:04:12,017
AS I EXPLAINED, THEY TOLD ME
IF I DIDN'T COME BACK,

63
00:04:12,019 --> 00:04:17,289
- THEY WERE WALKING.
- MEGHAN, YOUR CLIENTS
ARE LEAVING.

64
00:04:17,957 --> 00:04:20,859
OKAY, FOUR. FOUR,
AND WE GO TO CLOSE TODAY.

65
00:04:20,861 --> 00:04:25,163
<i>- NOW WOULD YOU PLEASE GO</i>
<i>GET THEM BEFORE THEY LEAVE?</i>
<i>- TELL MY CLIENTS</i>

66
00:04:25,165 --> 00:04:28,734
I'LL SEND THE PAPERWORK
OVER THIS AFTERNOON.

67
00:04:28,736 --> 00:04:30,569
OKAY.

68
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:36,241
IT'S BEEN A PLEASURE.

69
00:04:36,243 --> 00:04:38,577
THANK YOU.

70
00:04:38,845 --> 00:04:43,181
AND CONGRATULATIONS
ON A GREAT BUY.

71
00:04:50,757 --> 00:04:52,724
I JUST CLOSED
THE SMITH'S DEAL.

72
00:04:52,726 --> 00:04:56,028
GOOD. IT'S ABOUT TIME.
NO, I DON'T LIKE ANY OF IT.
REDO IT.

73
00:04:56,030 --> 00:05:00,732
YOU, COME WITH ME.
THERE'S SOME PEOPLE I WANT
YOU TO MEET IN MY OFFICE.

74
00:05:00,734 --> 00:05:05,103
MEGHAN, I WOULD LIKE
TO INTRODUCE YOU TO
THE YAKAMOTO BROTHERS,

75
00:05:05,105 --> 00:05:06,571
KANA AND HOSHI YAKAMOTO.

76
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:12,010
GENTLEMEN, THIS
IS MEGHAN DOHERTY.

77
00:05:12,012 --> 00:05:13,578
<i>KONICHIWA.</i>

78
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:14,980
<i>KONICHIWA.</i>

79
00:05:14,982 --> 00:05:16,548
[SPEAKS JAPANESE]

80
00:05:16,550 --> 00:05:19,951
<i>SHE WILL BE HEADING</i>
<i>YOUR CASINO PROJECT.</i>

81
00:05:19,953 --> 00:05:23,722
MR. WHITAKER, WE HAVE
A LOT RIDING ON OUR DEAL.

82
00:05:23,724 --> 00:05:27,726
I UNDERSTAND. MEGHAN IS
MY TOP INVESTMENT BANKER
HERE AT THE FIRM.

83
00:05:27,728 --> 00:05:29,428
WE'VE REVISED
OUR BUSINESS PLAN

84
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:33,365
TO INCLUDE PHOTOS
OF THE EXTENDED LAND
IN THE MOJAVE.

85
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:36,201
I HAVE BEEN ANTICIPATING
THESE PLANS FOR A FEW
WEEKS NOW.

86
00:05:36,203 --> 00:05:40,105
AND FOR OUT
NEXT MEETING, WE'LL
HAVE AN OUTLINE IDENTIFYING

87
00:05:40,107 --> 00:05:44,543
RISKS, AND FACTS
UNDERLINING YOUR INVESTMENT.

88
00:05:53,419 --> 00:05:54,086
NOW, THAT WAS DIFFERENT.

89
00:05:54,088 --> 00:05:56,855
TO SAY THE LEAST.
[LAUGHS]

90
00:05:56,857 --> 00:06:00,258
YOU HAVE YOUR WORK
CUT OUT FOR YOU NOW.

91
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:02,527
SO, ARE WE ALL
SET FOR TONIGHT?

92
00:06:02,529 --> 00:06:05,630
THE DECORATIONS ARE UP.
THE CATERERS START SERVING
AT 8:00.

93
00:06:05,632 --> 00:06:07,666
EVERYONE KNOWS TO BE
AT YOUR HOUSE BY 7:00

94
00:06:07,668 --> 00:06:09,334
OR DIE BY THE HANDS
OF MEGHAN DOHERTY.

95
00:06:09,336 --> 00:06:10,502
AND VALENTINA
KNOWS NOTHING?

96
00:06:10,504 --> 00:06:12,237
SHE THINKS
WE'RE DOING SUSHI.

97
00:06:12,239 --> 00:06:14,339
<i>[MAN ON SPEAKERPHONE]</i>
<i>I HEAR YOU'RE TRYING TO CLOSE</i>

98
00:06:14,341 --> 00:06:16,875
<i>ON THE YAKAMOTO BROTHERS</i>
<i>CASINO THING, RANDOLPH.</i>

99
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:19,745
YOU THINK SO, AL?
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

100
00:06:19,747 --> 00:06:21,813
YOU'VE BEEN TRYING TO SQUEEZE
OUR COMPANY FOR YEARS NOW,

101
00:06:21,815 --> 00:06:24,216
AND IT'S NOT GOING TO WORK.
WE'RE NOT GIVING IN.

102
00:06:24,218 --> 00:06:28,153
I CAN'T WAIT TO SHOW OFF
MY NEW OUTFIT TONIGHT.

103
00:06:28,155 --> 00:06:28,987
LIKE ALWAYS.

104
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:30,956
ARE YOU IMPLYING
THAT I'M SELF-CENTERED?

105
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:33,859
MMM, THAT'S RIGHT.
THE SAME SELF-CENTERED FRIEND

106
00:06:33,861 --> 00:06:37,429
WHO STUCK MY NECK OUT
TO GET YOU A JOB AT THE FIRM.

107
00:06:37,431 --> 00:06:38,697
HOW QUICKLY WE FORGET.

108
00:06:38,699 --> 00:06:40,232
<i>[AL] JUST REMEMBER ONE THING,</i>
<i>RANDOLPH.</i>

109
00:06:40,234 --> 00:06:43,535
<i>I AM IN FIRST POSITION</i>
<i>ON EDEN GRAHAM'S MOJAVE LAND.</i>

110
00:06:43,537 --> 00:06:44,870
<i>AND I WILL FORECLOSE</i>
<i>ON SATURDAY,</i>

111
00:06:44,872 --> 00:06:50,175
<i>AND WHEN I DO, THE YAKAMOTOS</i>
<i>WILL BE KNOCKING ON MY DOOR.</i>

112
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:51,877
<i>[BUZZING]</i>

113
00:06:51,879 --> 00:06:54,846
THAT'S THE OFFICE.
HOLD ON. HELLO?

114
00:06:54,848 --> 00:06:57,549
MEGHAN,
I NEED YOU HERE TONIGHT.

115
00:06:57,551 --> 00:06:59,484
TONIGHT?

116
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:01,253
[WHISPERS] IT'S
VALENTINA'S PARTY.

117
00:07:01,255 --> 00:07:05,657
SIR-- ALL RIGHT.
I'LL BE THERE
BY 6:00 PM, SIR.

118
00:07:05,659 --> 00:07:08,326
I'LL HAVE TIME TO STOP
AT JASON'S OF BEVERLY HILLS

119
00:07:08,328 --> 00:07:09,795
<i>BEFORE I MEET WITH WHITAKER.</i>

120
00:07:09,797 --> 00:07:13,331
<i>I WANT TO GET VALENTINA</i>
<i>SOMETHING SPECIAL.</i>

121
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:17,102
SO WHAT'S NEW
AT THE FIRM?

122
00:07:17,104 --> 00:07:19,237
I CLOSED A BIG ONE TODAY.

123
00:07:19,239 --> 00:07:21,173
<i>YOU DID? CONGRATULATIONS!</i>

124
00:07:21,175 --> 00:07:22,441
HOW'S YOUR CAR DEALERSHIP
GOING?

125
00:07:22,443 --> 00:07:27,512
<i>- DEALERSHIP IS GREAT.</i>
<i>-</i> THAT'S GORGEOUS. I HAVE
TO GET A GIFT FOR MT FRIEND.

126
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:31,016
AH, THAT'S BEAUTIFUL.

127
00:07:31,018 --> 00:07:32,451
ANY INTERESTING OPPORTUNITIES
YOU CAN THROW MY WAY?

128
00:07:32,453 --> 00:07:37,122
YEAH. ONE OF MY CLIENTS IS
THINKING OF OPENING A CHAIN
OF AUTOMATIC CAR WASHES.

129
00:07:37,124 --> 00:07:39,224
THAT SOUNDS INTERESTING.
I KNOW I DID REAL WELL

130
00:07:39,226 --> 00:07:43,695
INVESTING IN
THE LAST EXOTIC CAR
BUSINESS YOU GOT ME TURNED ON

131
00:07:43,697 --> 00:07:45,297
SO HOW MUCH?

132
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:46,465
FOR YOU, 8,000.

133
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:48,333
THAT'S RETAIL.
WHAT'S MY PRICE?

134
00:07:48,335 --> 00:07:51,470
OKAY, I'LL DO 7,500.

135
00:07:52,672 --> 00:07:54,973
OKAY. 7,000.
BUT THAT'S IT.

136
00:07:54,975 --> 00:07:56,608
DEAL.

137
00:07:56,876 --> 00:08:00,645
- HOW MUCH FOR THAT ONE?
- NORMALLY IT'S 2,000,
BUT

138
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:01,980
FOR YOU, 1,500.

139
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:03,181
COULD YOU BOX THAT ALSO?

140
00:08:03,183 --> 00:08:06,117
SURE. SO HOW'S THE FERRARI?

141
00:08:06,119 --> 00:08:06,852
FAST.

142
00:08:06,854 --> 00:08:08,019
YOU KNOW,
THAT'S THE ONLY CAR

143
00:08:08,021 --> 00:08:09,254
I DON'T HAVE
IN MY DEALERSHIP,

144
00:08:09,256 --> 00:08:12,123
SO IF YOU EVER WANT TO GET
THAT THING OFF YOUR HANDS,
LET ME KNOW.

145
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:14,459
LET GO OF MY PRIDE AND JOY?
NEVER.

146
00:08:14,461 --> 00:08:18,797
JASON, YOU KNOW BETTER
THAN TO ASK ME THAT.

147
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:22,567
<i>[WHITAKER] THE MOJAVE DESERT.</i>

148
00:08:22,569 --> 00:08:28,273
<i>5,000 ACRES OF THE MOJAVE</i>
<i>DESERT.</i>

149
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:32,477
WE ARE GOING TO BUILD
A CASINO RESORT,

150
00:08:32,479 --> 00:08:36,481
INCLUDING AN
18-HOLE GOLF COURSE

151
00:08:36,483 --> 00:08:37,749
AND A COUNTRY CLUB.

152
00:08:37,751 --> 00:08:39,518
SO WHAT'S THE CATCH?

153
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:45,056
WELL, GRAEME MINISTRIES
OWNS 1,000 ACRES

154
00:08:45,058 --> 00:08:47,392
RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE OF IT.

155
00:08:47,394 --> 00:08:50,729
THE YAKAMOTO BROTHERS
ARE GOING TO NEED

156
00:08:50,731 --> 00:08:56,268
THIS ONE PIECE OF LAND
TO BUILD THEIR VISION UPON.

157
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:59,971
NOW, THIS LAND IS ALREADY IN
FORECLOSURE,

158
00:08:59,973 --> 00:09:03,542
BUT THE OWNER,
MR. EDEN GRAHAM,

159
00:09:03,544 --> 00:09:05,510
IS NOT COOPERATING.

160
00:09:05,512 --> 00:09:09,614
AND SO, THIS LAND

161
00:09:09,616 --> 00:09:12,284
IS GOING TO
GO TO AUCTION
NEXT SATURDAY.

162
00:09:12,286 --> 00:09:13,685
THAT DOESN'T GIVE
US MUCH TIME.

163
00:09:13,687 --> 00:09:17,455
I KNOW. THIS GUY
ABSOLUTELY REFUSES
TO SELL.

164
00:09:17,457 --> 00:09:21,726
THEREFORE I NEED YOU
TO DRIVE UP TO THE MOJAVE,

165
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:23,495
AND MEET WITH
MR. EDEN GRAHAM.

166
00:09:23,497 --> 00:09:28,466
MEGHAN, YOU
CLOSE ON THIS DEAL,

167
00:09:28,468 --> 00:09:32,103
AND WE'LL ENJOY
A CELEBRATION TOGETHER.

168
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:34,105
MY DREAM WILL BE REALIZED

169
00:09:34,107 --> 00:09:39,778
AND GUESS WHO WILL BE
IN LINE TO FILL MY SHOES?

170
00:09:52,358 --> 00:09:54,025
HI!

171
00:09:54,027 --> 00:09:56,094
VALENTINA.

172
00:09:56,096 --> 00:09:57,762
I'M SORRY I MISSED
YOUR PARTY.

173
00:09:57,764 --> 00:09:59,464
NO, YOU DIDN'T MISS IT.
YOU'RE HERE NOW,

174
00:09:59,466 --> 00:10:01,099
AND THIS IS
HOW IT SHOULD BE,

175
00:10:01,101 --> 00:10:02,367
THREE BEST FRIENDS,
ENJOYING EACH OTHER.

176
00:10:02,369 --> 00:10:07,005
I KNEW WHEN WHITAKER
CALLED YOU TO HIS OFFICE
IT WOULD BE A LATE NIGHT.

177
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:09,407
WE ALL KNEW THAT.

178
00:10:12,044 --> 00:10:13,011
WE DECIDED
TO WAIT FOR YOU.

179
00:10:13,013 --> 00:10:16,848
OH, GUYS,
YOU ARE SO SWEET.

180
00:10:16,850 --> 00:10:20,051
OH, I'M ACTING AS IF
IT'S MY BIRTHDAY. HERE.

181
00:10:20,053 --> 00:10:23,989
OH MY, LOOK
AT THIS BRACELET!

182
00:10:23,991 --> 00:10:26,291
IT'S SO BEAUTIFUL!

183
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:27,826
OKAY, OPEN.

184
00:10:27,828 --> 00:10:29,327
OKAY!

185
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,497
OH!

186
00:10:32,632 --> 00:10:33,898
DO YOU LIKE IT?

187
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,066
I LOVE IT!

188
00:10:35,068 --> 00:10:36,901
OH, THANK YOU.

189
00:10:36,903 --> 00:10:40,271
LOOK WHAT ADAM GOT ME.

190
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,040
THAT IS GORGEOUS!

191
00:10:42,042 --> 00:10:44,976
<i>YOU MUST HAVE SPENT</i>
<i>YOUR ENTIRE PAYCHECK</i>
<i>ON THAT.</i>

192
00:10:44,978 --> 00:10:47,212
NOT ALL OF IT,
BUT, YEAH, MOST.

193
00:10:47,214 --> 00:10:49,414
<i>[PHONE BUZZES]</i>

194
00:10:52,184 --> 00:10:53,118
HI, MOM.

195
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:55,286
I FINALLY CAUGHT YOU.

196
00:10:55,288 --> 00:10:56,021
LET ME TALK TO HER.

197
00:10:56,023 --> 00:10:58,123
MOM, I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
A CALL BACK TOMORROW.

198
00:10:58,125 --> 00:11:02,427
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO
CALL ME BACK YESTERDAY.

199
00:11:02,429 --> 00:11:05,897
GOOD NIGHT. I LOVE YOU.

200
00:11:06,565 --> 00:11:09,234
SHE HAS
THE WORST TIMING.

201
00:11:09,236 --> 00:11:09,701
HMM.

202
00:11:09,703 --> 00:11:13,171
<i>[MEGHAN] I HAVE THE BIGGEST</i>
<i>DEAL OF MY LIFE AND SHE CALLS</i>
<i>TO CHIT CHAT?</i>

203
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:17,075
DON'T BE SELFISH.
IT'S YOUR MOTHER.

204
00:11:17,077 --> 00:11:20,078
<i>YOU CAN'T TAKE TWO MINUTES</i>
<i>OF YOUR TIME?</i>

205
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,514
TWO MINUTES WILL
TURN INTO TWO HOURS.

206
00:11:22,516 --> 00:11:25,784
I JUST HAVE SO MUCH ON MY MIND
WITH THE YAKAMOTO ACCOUNT.

207
00:11:25,786 --> 00:11:27,686
MEGHAN, EVER SINCE
I'VE KNOWN YOU,

208
00:11:27,688 --> 00:11:30,822
ALL YOU CARE ABOUT IS MONEY
AND YOUR CAREER.

209
00:11:30,824 --> 00:11:33,124
WHAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN
WHEN YOU TURN 60?

210
00:11:33,126 --> 00:11:36,795
YOU'RE GOING TO WISH THAT
SOMEONE WOULD CALL AND VISIT
YOU.

211
00:11:36,797 --> 00:11:40,765
AND GUESS WHAT? YOU ARE
GOING TO BE ALL ALONE.

212
00:11:40,767 --> 00:11:42,701
YOU ARE JUST AS OLD AS I AM.

213
00:11:42,703 --> 00:11:43,568
BUT I LOVE MY FAMILY.

214
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:48,339
AND ONE DAY I PLAN TO
SETTLE DOWN AND HAVE
CHILDREN OF MY OWN

215
00:11:48,341 --> 00:11:49,674
SO THAT WHEN I GET OLD
I'LL HAVE SOMEONE TO LOVE ME.

216
00:11:49,676 --> 00:11:55,547
LOOK AT YOU! YOU DON'T DATE
AND YOU HAVE NO FRIENDS
OUTSIDE OF ADAM AND ME.

217
