00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:44,408
A TOUR IS NOT GOING TO CHANGE
THE POSITION YOU'RE IN.

437
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:48,512
COME ON. WHAT DO YOU
HAVE TO LOSE?

438
00:25:54,052 --> 00:25:56,487
[MOTOR STARTS]

439
00:26:10,569 --> 00:26:11,268
HMMM.

440
00:26:11,270 --> 00:26:15,205
<i>I'M SECOND-GENERATION</i>
<i>LAND OWNER OF GRAHAM HOLDINGS.</i>

441
00:26:15,207 --> 00:26:15,940
<i>MY DAD WAS A MINISTER.</i>

442
00:26:15,942 --> 00:26:17,508
I USE THIS LAND
TO GIVE BACK TO GOD,

443
00:26:17,510 --> 00:26:23,447
FOR ME REBELLING AGAINST
HIS RIGHTEOUS WAYS WHEN
I WAS A KID.

444
00:26:26,685 --> 00:26:28,252
LOOK AT IT.

445
00:26:28,254 --> 00:26:32,356
<i>I LOVE THIS LAND.</i>

446
00:26:33,158 --> 00:26:35,593
THERE'S NO PLACE LIKE IT.

447
00:26:35,595 --> 00:26:40,965
OUR MINISTRY HAS TAKEN
A BIG HIT, JUST AS I'M
SURE RESIDENTIAL HAS.

448
00:26:40,967 --> 00:26:43,567
CHURCHES CAN'T TITHE
THE WAY THEY USED TO

449
00:26:43,569 --> 00:26:45,269
OR PAY EXTRAS FOR THE KIDS,

450
00:26:45,271 --> 00:26:48,372
AND THAT TRICKLES DOWN
TO PEOPLE LIKE US.

451
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:55,379
MEGHAN YOU CAN TELL WHITAKER
I HAVE TO DECLINE HIS OFFER.

452
00:26:56,815 --> 00:26:59,116
LISTEN, THE DEAL
IS THE DEAL.

453
00:26:59,118 --> 00:27:02,086
YOU CAN PRAY TO YOUR GOD
ANY TIME, DAY OR NIGHT,

454
00:27:02,088 --> 00:27:07,458
BUT IT'S NOT GONNA STOP
THE FACT THAT OUT BANK
IS GONNA TAKE THIS PROPERTY.

455
00:27:07,559 --> 00:27:10,160
<i>TAKE ME BACK TO MY CAR.</i>

456
00:27:22,007 --> 00:27:25,476
MEGHAN, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

457
00:27:25,478 --> 00:27:29,546
I'D BE WILLING TO PUT MY FAITH
THAT GOD WILL COME THROUGH

458
00:27:29,548 --> 00:27:31,448
AND THIS WILL ALL BE
WATER UNDER THE BRIDGE.

459
00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:36,754
IF YOU'LL JUST STAY HERE
FOR SIX DAYS.

460
00:27:37,322 --> 00:27:38,789
SEE WHAT IT IS WE DO HERE.

461
00:27:38,791 --> 00:27:40,491
WATCH GOD'S BLESSINGS UNFOLD.

462
00:27:40,493 --> 00:27:46,764
AND THEN IF BY SOME CHANCE
YOU DON'T SEE WHY THIS LAND
IS SO IMPORTANT,

463
00:27:46,766 --> 00:27:50,167
I'LL SIGN YOUR DEAL BEFORE
THE LAND GOES TO AUCTION

464
00:27:50,169 --> 00:27:52,836
SO YOU CAN GET YOUR
BIG COMMISSION CHECK.

465
00:27:52,838 --> 00:27:55,739
LISTEN, TAKE THE CHECK,

466
00:27:55,741 --> 00:27:57,474
GATHER YOUR CHRISTIAN FOLK,

467
00:27:57,476 --> 00:28:01,779
AND GO BUILD A CHURCH
IN A NEW LOCATION.

468
00:28:02,047 --> 00:28:05,783
NEAR A CITY WHERE
PEOPLE ACTUALLY LIVE.

469
00:28:07,252 --> 00:28:07,985
MS. DOHERTY,

470
00:28:07,987 --> 00:28:11,088
I KNOW AS LONG AS I
DON'T PUT MY SIGNATURE
ON THAT DOCUMENT,

471
00:28:11,090 --> 00:28:14,792
I HAVE A FIGHTING
CHANCE TO KEEP WHAT'S
RIGHTFULLY MINE.

472
00:28:14,794 --> 00:28:19,029
NO, IT'S NOT OVER
TILL GOD SAYS IT'S OVER.

473
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:22,633
AND GOD HASN'T
TOLD ME ANYTHING.

474
00:28:23,101 --> 00:28:24,034
ALL RIGHT.

475
00:28:24,036 --> 00:28:28,672
SO, WHY WOULD ME STAYING HERE
FOR SIX DAYS

476
00:28:28,674 --> 00:28:31,241
MAKE ANY DIFFERENCE IN WHETHER
OR NOT YOU SIGN THIS DEAL?

477
00:28:31,243 --> 00:28:34,445
YOU'LL BE ABLE TO SEE
WHAT WE DO HERE WITH
YOUR OWN EYES.

478
00:28:34,447 --> 00:28:39,283
MAYBE THEN YOU'LL UNDERSTAND
WHY I'M WILLING TO PUT MY
FAITH IN GOD

479
00:28:39,285 --> 00:28:42,486
AND FIGHT TO KEEP
THIS PLACE OPEN
TO HELP PEOPLE IN NEED.

480
00:28:42,488 --> 00:28:47,891
TO YOU, THIS IS JUST
ANOTHER BUSINESS DEAL.
THIS IS MY WHOLE LIFE.

481
00:28:47,893 --> 00:28:52,129
IF IT'S MORE MONEY YOU WANT,
LET ME CALL MR. WHITAKER.
LET'S UP THE OFFER.

482
00:28:52,131 --> 00:28:59,336
YOU HAVE MY OFFER.
SIX DAYS AND I'LL SIGN. THAT'S
MY PROMISE TO YOU AND TO GOD.

483
00:28:59,338 --> 00:29:02,940
ONE CONDITION. THE DEAL
REMAINS BETWEEN YOU AND ME.

484
00:29:02,942 --> 00:29:03,807
YOU CAN'T TELL ANYBODY ELSE.

485
00:29:03,809 --> 00:29:06,276
I DON'T WANT PEOPLE
AROUND HERE TO JUDGE
OR TREAT YOU

486
00:29:06,278 --> 00:29:09,913
ANY DIFFERENTLY THAN
THE REST OF THE GUESTS.

487
00:29:15,019 --> 00:29:16,620
ALL RIGHT.

488
00:29:16,622 --> 00:29:19,389
DEAL.

489
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:22,893
OKAY.

490
00:29:22,895 --> 00:29:26,430
I JUST NEED
TO MAKE A FEW CALLS.

491
00:29:38,476 --> 00:29:41,445
[BEEPING]

492
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:47,718
MEGHAN.

493
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:48,118
[GASPS]

494
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:51,488
YOU SCARED THE LIVING
DAYLIGHTS OUT OF ME.

495
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:53,891
SORRY. WE HAVE A CAMP
MEETING IN FIVE MINUTES.

496
00:29:53,893 --> 00:29:58,829
ABOUT THIS DEAL,
I NEED TO GO AND MAKE
A CALL TO MY OFFICE.

497
00:29:58,831 --> 00:30:00,931
I NEED TO GO HOME AND
GET SOME EXTRA CLOTHING,

498
00:30:00,933 --> 00:30:03,400
BECAUSE THE ONLY CLOTHING
I HAVE IS WHAT I'M WEARING.

499
00:30:03,402 --> 00:30:06,737
<i>NOW, DO YOU HAVE A PHONE</i>
<i>IN YOUR OFFICE I CAN USE?</i>

500
00:30:06,739 --> 00:30:09,273
FIVE MINUTES. AND YOU
CAN LEAVE ALL YOUR STUFF
IN THE CAR.

501
00:30:09,275 --> 00:30:13,610
NO ONE'S GONNA MESS
WITH IT. FIVE MINUTES.

502
00:30:20,752 --> 00:30:22,085
[PHONE BEEPING]

503
00:30:22,087 --> 00:30:27,257
HASN'T ANYONE EVER TOLD THEM
THAT STARING ISN'T POLITE?

504
00:30:29,060 --> 00:30:33,197
MEGHAN, LISTEN,
WHY DON'T YOU JOIN MY
CHURCH'S CONGREGATION?

505
00:30:33,199 --> 00:30:34,398
YOU CAN BE
OUR SPECIAL GUEST.

506
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:39,069
MAYBE YOU COULD TEACH MY KIDS
A LITTLE SOMETHING ABOUT
WHATEVER IT IS THAT YOU DO.

507
00:30:39,071 --> 00:30:40,671
THEY LOVE YOUR CAR.

508
00:30:40,673 --> 00:30:42,406
SURE. WHATEVER YOU SAY.

509
00:30:42,408 --> 00:30:43,607
AWESOME. THANK YOU.

510
00:30:43,609 --> 00:30:44,241
[BEEPING]

511
00:30:44,243 --> 00:30:48,312
I GUESS SOMEBODY DIDN'T GET
THE MEMO ABOUT APPROPRIATE
ATTIRE.

512
00:30:48,314 --> 00:30:50,848
I'M JACOB. EVERYONE
AROUND HERE CALLS ME JAKE.

513
00:30:50,850 --> 00:30:55,485
WELL, JACOB, YOU CAN
KEEP YOUR SMART COMMENTS
TO YOURSELF.

514
00:30:55,487 --> 00:30:57,621
LOOK, I JUST SAW YOU WALK
IN HERE WITH MY FATHER,

515
00:30:57,623 --> 00:30:59,256
AND I CAN TELL BY THE
WAY THAT YOU'RE DRESSED

516
00:30:59,258 --> 00:31:02,559
THAT YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY NOT ONE
OF THE CHURCH GROUP LEADERS.

517
00:31:02,561 --> 00:31:03,360
SO, WHY ARE YOU HERE?

518
00:31:03,362 --> 00:31:07,130
I'M HERE FOR THE SAME REASON
AS EVERYONE ELSE.
ENLIGHTENMENT.

519
00:31:07,132 --> 00:31:09,266
NOW I DON'T KNOW
WHO YOU ARE, BUT--

520
00:31:09,268 --> 00:31:13,070
I'M SORRY, DID YOU JUST SAY
THAT WAS YOUR FATHER?

521
00:31:13,072 --> 00:31:15,572
YEAH. I RUN THIS PLACE
WITH MY PARENTS.

522
00:31:15,574 --> 00:31:18,175
I'M THE HEAD COUNSELOR HERE.

523
00:31:18,177 --> 00:31:19,810
SORRY. MEGHAN DOHERTY.

524
00:31:19,812 --> 00:31:24,248
HELLO, EVERYONE.
WELCOME TO GOD'S COUNTRY.

525
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:28,452
I WANT YOU TO SHAKE AWAY
ALL THE WORRIES OF YOUR
DAY-TO-DAY RAT RACE

526
00:31:28,454 --> 00:31:31,722
AND PEER PRESSURE, AND
ESPECIALLY VIDEO GAMES,

527
00:31:31,724 --> 00:31:33,323
SOCIAL NETWORKING, AND UH--

528
00:31:33,325 --> 00:31:34,625
[PHONE BEEPS]

529
00:31:34,627 --> 00:31:36,760
TEXTING.
[CLEARS THROAT]

530
00:31:36,762 --> 00:31:38,795
YOU'RE HERE TO RELAX,
MAKE FRIENDS,

531
00:31:38,797 --> 00:31:43,433
AND MOST OF ALL, DISCOVER
THAT REAL INNER LOVE OF SELF
AND GOD'S SPIRIT.

532
00:31:43,435 --> 00:31:48,906
BEFORE WE BEGIN, I WANT YOU
TO TURN TO THE PERSON
TO YOUR RIGHT AND LEFT,

533
00:31:48,908 --> 00:31:52,509
AND GIVE THEM A BIG
WELCOMING HUG.

534
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:55,946
HEY.
OH!

535
00:31:59,651 --> 00:32:01,051
OKAY.

536
00:32:01,053 --> 00:32:03,120
OH MY--
[GIRL SQUEALS]

537
00:32:03,122 --> 00:32:03,687
[GRAHAM LAUGHS]

538
00:32:03,689 --> 00:32:08,358
MEGHAN, I'D LIKE TO INTRODUCE
MY BETTER HALF OVER HERE

539
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:12,162
FOR ALMOST 25 YEARS NOW,
CAROLINE.

540
00:32:12,164 --> 00:32:15,299
SHE'S SORT OF THE MOTHER HEN,
CARETAKER OF THE CAMP.

541
00:32:15,301 --> 00:32:20,404
SO IF YOU GET SICK, BITTEN,
OR JUST PLAIN HOMESICK,
SHE'S--

542
00:32:20,406 --> 00:32:21,138
HONEY, STOP IT.
BITTEN?

543
00:32:21,140 --> 00:32:24,141
HE'S JUST PULLING YOUR LEG.
IF IT WAS THE SUMMER TIME,
YES,

544
00:32:24,143 --> 00:32:27,844
BUT IN THE COOLER MONTHS
WE DON'T HAVE THAT PROBLEM.

545
00:32:27,846 --> 00:32:29,146
GOOD TO KNOW.

546
00:32:29,148 --> 00:32:30,180
OH, HEY, MEGHAN,
THIS IS GERI.

547
00:32:30,182 --> 00:32:34,251
- SHE'S ONE OF THE COUNSELORS
HERE. YOU GUYS SHOULD--
- HI.

548
00:32:34,253 --> 00:32:35,485
ARE YOU A MODEL?

549
00:32:35,487 --> 00:32:36,486
YOU'RE SO PRETTY.

550
00:32:36,488 --> 00:32:39,222
I KNOW YOUR FEET MUST BE
KILLING YOU IN THOSE
HIGH HEELS.

551
00:32:39,224 --> 00:32:40,557
GERI, GO FETCH MEGHAN
A PAIR OF YOUR BOOTS.

552
00:32:40,559 --> 00:32:42,893
- NO.
- THEY'LL PROBABLY
BE A LITTLE TOO BIG,

553
00:32:42,895 --> 00:32:45,696
BUT THEY'LL GIVE YOUR FEET
A MUCH NEEDED REST.

554
00:32:45,698 --> 00:32:51,535
JUST SHOW ME TO MY ROOM
SO I CAN GET ON MY LAPTOP
AND MAKE A FEW CALLS,

555
00:32:51,537 --> 00:32:52,803
AND I'LL BE AWESOME.

556
00:32:52,805 --> 00:32:53,370
[ALL LAUGHING]

557
00:32:53,372 --> 00:32:57,374
MEGHAN, YOU'RE KIND OF MISSING
THE POINT OF WHAT WE DO HERE
IN GOD'S COUNTRY.

558
00:32:57,376 --> 00:32:58,976
AND THAT IS--

559
00:32:58,978 --> 00:33:00,377
OFF THE GRID.

560
00:33:00,379 --> 00:33:01,712
HERE YOU GO.

561
00:33:01,714 --> 00:33:03,780
ANYWAY, WELCOME ABOARD.

562
00:33:03,782 --> 00:33:07,417
GRUDGE MATCH. PING PONG.
LET'S GO. WANT TO WATCH?

563
00:33:07,419 --> 00:33:08,452
I'M GONNA WATCH.

564
00:33:08,454 --> 00:33:10,220
THOSE ARE FOR YOU.

565
00:33:10,222 --> 00:33:11,588
I'LL TAKE YOU
TO YOUR TRAILER.

566
00:33:11,590 --> 00:33:13,090
YOU'RE GONNA WANT THOSE.

567
00:33:13,092 --> 00:33:14,524
I'M NOT WEARING THEM.

568
00:33:14,526 --> 00:33:17,260
MY TRAILER?

569
00:33:19,330 --> 00:33:21,798
[PAINED GROAN]

570
00:33:29,741 --> 00:33:30,774
WHAT IS THIS?

571
00:33:30,776 --> 00:33:32,743
<i>THIS IS YOUR LIVING QUARTERS.</i>

572
00:33:32,745 --> 00:33:34,411
<i>SORRY IT'S NOT</i>
<i>THE PLAZA HOTEL.</i>

573
00:33:34,413 --> 00:33:37,014
I AM NOT STAYING IN THAT.

574
00:33:37,016 --> 00:33:43,653
WELL,
IT'S STAY IN THAT TRAILER,
OR IN THE HOUSE WITH ALL

575
00:33:45,490 --> 00:33:47,958
HERE OR THERE.

576
00:34:09,113 --> 00:34:12,749
WHAT HAVE I GOTTEN
MYSELF INTO?

577
00:34:27,065 --> 00:34:29,199
GROSS!

578
00:34:30,368 --> 00:34:31,435
<i>[GASPS]</i>

579
00:34:31,437 --> 00:34:33,737
[SCREAMS]

580
00:34:33,739 --> 00:34:36,440
GET OFF!

581
00:34:39,844 --> 00:34:42,312
<i>[COYOTE HOWLING]</i>

582
00:34:49,987 --> 00:34:51,421
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
STALKING ME?

583
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:54,291
NO, I JUST CAME BY
TO SEE IF YOU WERE OKAY.

584
00:34:54,293 --> 00:34:55,559
I AM NOT OKAY!

585
00:34:55,561 --> 00:34:59,696
I HEAR THESE THINGS
HOWLING AT ME AND
THERE WAS THIS BIG BUG--

586
00:34:59,698 --> 00:35:01,364
WAIT. A BUG?

587
00:35:01,366 --> 00:35:05,335
YES! ARE YOU LAUGHING AT ME?

588
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:08,305
WAIT A MINUTE.

589
00:35:08,307 --> 00:35:09,706
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

590
00:35:09,708 --> 00:35:12,209
HEY, MOM?
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPS]

591
00:35:12,211 --> 00:35:12,943
<i>YEAH, HONEY.</i>

592
00:35:12,945 --> 00:35:15,612
CAN YOU SEND GERI TO
TRAILER NUMBER ONE, PLEASE?

593
00:35:15,614 --> 00:35:18,148
<i>WHAT'S UP, JAKE?</i>

594
00:35:18,150 --> 00:35:21,785
IT'S MEGHAN.
AND A BUG.

595
00:35:21,787 --> 00:35:22,986
IT WAS A BIG BUG.
BIG.

596
00:35:22,988 --> 00:35:28,091
SORRY. A BIG BUG ATTACKED HER,
AND NOW SHE REFUSES TO GO
TO THE TRAILER.

597
00:35:28,093 --> 00:35:30,260
<i>YOU WANT ME TO SEND SOMEONE</i>
<i>TO STAY WITH HER?</i>

598
00:35:30,262 --> 00:35:34,898
- AFFIRMATIVE.
-  <i>OKAY, HONEY. I'LL TELL GERI.</i>
<i>BYE BYE.</i>

599
00:35:36,100 --> 00:35:37,601
THANKS.

600
00:35:41,672 --> 00:35:45,275
IT WAS A BIG, BIG BUG.

601
00:35:45,277 --> 00:35:48,578
IT'S ALL CLEAR.

602
00:35:48,580 --> 00:35:50,447
HI AGAIN.

603
00:35:50,449 --> 00:35:52,015
ARE YOU ALWAYS SO PETULANT?

604
00:35:52,017 --> 00:35:56,286
OH.
THEY ACTUALLY SAID THAT YOU
NEEDED A LITTLE HELP OUT HERE

605
00:35:56,288 --> 00:35:58,288
SO WE'RE GONNA BE
ROOMMATES NOW.

606
00:35:58,290 --> 00:35:59,456
I HOPE THAT'S OKAY.

607
00:35:59,458 --> 00:36:00,790
YOU'RE NOT TOO ADJUSTED
TO THE WILD, HUH?

608
00:36:00,792 --> 00:36:05,061
- THAT'S OKAY.
- WELL, NOW YOU HAVE
YOUR BODYGUARD.

609
00:36:05,063 --> 00:36:06,730
THANK YOU.

610
00:36:07,298 --> 00:36:08,965
OKAY.

611
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:11,234
OKAY, THIS IS FOR YOU.

612
00:36:11,236 --> 00:36:12,269
WHAT IS THIS?

613
00:36:12,271 --> 00:36:15,172
MR. GRAHAM SAID THAT YOU
NEEDED SOME CLOTHES TO WEAR,

614
00:36:15,174 --> 00:36:17,040
SO I JUST BROUGHT YOU
SOME OF MY OWN.

615
00:36:17,042 --> 00:36:20,010
I'M NOT WEARING THAT.

616
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:25,282
WE DON'T GET ANY SIGNALS
OUT HERE.

617
00:36:25,284 --> 00:36:27,884
WHAT, ARE YOU GUYS
IN THE 1800's?

618
00:36:27,886 --> 00:36:29,786
HOW DO YOU
LIVE LIKE THIS?

619
00:36:29,788 --> 00:36:30,320
LIVE LIKE WHAT?

620
00:36:30,322 --> 00:36:32,889
LIKE THIS. NO CELL PHONE,
WI-FI.

621
00:36:32,891 --> 00:36:34,791
WHAT ARE YOU
SUPPOSED TO BE PROVING?

622
00:36:34,793 --> 00:36:36,726
WE'RE NOT TRYING
TO PROVE ANYTHING.

623
00:36:36,728 --> 00:36:40,697
WE'RE ACTUALLY JUST
IN THE MIDDLE OF NOWHERE.

624
00:36:43,467 --> 00:36:44,367
WHAT?
HEY, MEGHAN.

625
00:36:44,369 --> 00:36:48,605
DO YOU MIND IF WE JUST SAY
A QUICK PRAYER BEFORE WE
HEAD IN FOR THE NIGHT?

626
00:36:48,607 --> 00:36:50,140
PRAY ON.

627
00:36:50,142 --> 00:36:51,975
OKAY.

628
00:36:54,745 --> 00:36:55,378
<i>[PHONE RINGING]</i>

629
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:57,914
<i>YOU'VE REACHED MEGHAN DOHERTY.</i>
<i>PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE.</i>

630
00:36:57,916 --> 00:37:01,551
MEGHAN, BET YOU WRAPPED
GRAHAM AND THOSE DOCUMENTS

631
00:37:01,553 --> 00:37:02,852
AROUND YOUR
LITTLE FINGER TODAY.

632
00:37:02,854 --> 00:37:06,089
I CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR
ABOUT IT. CALL ME.

633
00:37:12,930 --> 00:37:14,965
<i>[GERI] MEGHAN, WAKE UP!</i>

634
00:37:14,967 --> 00:37:16,900
MEGHAN. MEGHAN. MEGHAN.

635
00:37:16,902 --> 00:37:19,703
WAKE UP, SLEEPYHEAD!
[MEGHAN SNORES]

636
00:37:20,137 --> 00:37:20,737
<i>♪ RISE AND SHINE</i>

637
00:37:20,739 --> 00:37:24,207
<i>♪ AND KICK OUT</i>
<i>THE GLORY, GLORY  ♪</i>

638
00:37:24,209 --> 00:37:25,575
WHAT TIME IS IT?

639
00:37:25,577 --> 00:37:26,710
IT'S 6:00.

640
00:37:26,712 --> 00:37:28,144
6:00 A.M.?

641
00:37:28,146 --> 00:37:28,712
YEAH.

642
00:37:28,714 --> 00:37:34,918
COME BACK AT 10:00 A.M.
I DON'T DO BREAKFAST.

643
00:37:43,060 --> 00:37:45,762
GERI, WHERE'S MEGHAN?

644
00:37:45,764 --> 00:37:48,665
SHE WOULDN'T GET UP.

645
00:37:50,601 --> 00:37:55,071
JAKE, WILL YOU ASK PASTOR
TINSLEY TO START THIS
MORNING'S PRAYER SERVICE?

646
00:37:55,073 --> 00:37:56,339
YEAH, YOU GOT IT.

647
00:37:56,341 --> 00:37:58,875
THANKS. BE RIGHT BACK.

648
00:37:58,976 --> 00:38:03,146
ALL RIGHT, Y'ALL, HOW'S
EVERYBODY DOING TODAY?

649
00:38:08,085 --> 00:38:10,020
<i>[CLANGING]</i>

650
00:38:10,022 --> 00:38:11,655
[SCREAMS]

651
00:38:18,396 --> 00:38:19,262
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

652
00:38:19,264 --> 00:38:20,997
WE'RE HAVING PRAYER
BEFORE BREAKFAST

653
00:38:20,999 --> 00:38:22,666
AND YOU HAVE TO JOIN
YOUR ASSIGNED GROUP.

654
00:38:22,668 --> 00:38:25,835
LISTEN. I'M TIRED. I
AM NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

655
00:38:25,837 --> 00:38:29,606
AND I HAVE AGREED TO
STAY HERE FOR SIX DAYS.

656
00:38:29,608 --> 00:38:30,073
[YAWNS]

657
00:38:30,075 --> 00:38:32,309
YOU AGREED TO BE PART
OF THE JOURNEY.

658
00:38:32,311 --> 00:38:34,711
BEING PART OF THE JOURNEY
MEANS TAKING THE JOURNEY.

659
00:38:34,713 --> 00:38:38,415
NOW IF YOU DON'T SHOW UP
FOR YOUR ASSIGNED GROUP,
OUR AGREEMENT'S OFF.

660
00:38:38,417 --> 00:38:42,686
YOU CAN GET BACK IN YOUR
FANCY CAR AND DRIVE BACK
TO LOS ANGELES TODAY.

661
00:38:42,688 --> 00:38:47,223
OKAY. I GET YOUR
POINT. LET ME JUST
GO TAKE A SHOWER--

662
00:38:47,225 --> 00:38:52,896
NO TIME FOR THAT.
YOU GOTTA MEET YOUR GROUP.
BREAKFAST IS IN 15 MINUTES.

663
00:38:52,898 --> 00:38:57,801
GET UP,
THROW SOME WATER ON YOUR
FACE, I'LL SEE YOU OUT HERE.

664
00:39:10,481 --> 00:39:13,683
JAKE, DO WE KNOW
WHERE YOUR FATHER IS?

665
00:39:16,554 --> 00:39:18,355
THERE SHE IS.

666
00:39:53,324 --> 00:39:57,093
MEGHAN, I THOUGHT WE COULD
ALL SIT DOWN TOGETHER,

667
00:39:57,095 --> 00:39:59,362
AND EAT AS A FAMILY.

668
00:40:03,601 --> 00:40:06,970
LET'S BOW OUR HEADS
IN PRAYER.

669
00:40:06,972 --> 00:40:10,206
AND JESUS SAID UNTO THEM,
"I AM THE BREAD OF LIFE,

670
00:40:10,208 --> 00:40:13,042
HE THAT COMETH TO ME
SHALL NEVER HUNGER

671
00:40:13,044 --> 00:40:17,180
AND HE THAT BELIEVETH
ON ME SHALL NEVER THIRST.

672
00:40:17,182 --> 00:40:19,315
[ALL] AMEN.
AMEN.

673
00:40:19,317 --> 00:40:21,484
NOW WE CAN EAT.

674
00:40:26,424 --> 00:40:29,993
ALL RIGHT, GANG, REMEMBER
THIS IS A CONTEST

675
00:40:29,995 --> 00:40:31,227
SO THERE ARE SPECIAL
REWARD ACTIVITIES

676
00:40:31,229 --> 00:40:33,496
FOR THE GROUP THAT
PULLS TOGETHER AND
DOES THE BEST JOB.

677
00:40:33,498 --> 00:40:38,134
THE FIRST ACTIVITY IS
A TWO-MILE HIKE UP TO
THE TENNIS COURTS.

678
00:40:38,136 --> 00:40:40,637
LENNY, IT'S ALL YOU, BUDDY.

679
00:40:40,639 --> 00:40:41,571
WAIT.

680
00:40:41,573 --> 00:40:42,138
YOU ALL RIGHT?

681
00:40:42,140 --> 00:40:44,874
I AM NOT DRESSED
FOR A TWO-MILE HIKE
OUT IN THIS JUNGLE.

682
00:40:44,876 --> 00:40:47,010
I'D ACTUALLY BE MORE
WORRIED ABOUT THE SNAKES.

683
00:40:47,012 --> 00:40:52,449
[LAUGHS]
COME ON, I'M JUST
KIDDING WITH YOU.

684
00:40:52,451 --> 00:40:54,717
I GOT YOUR BACK.

685
00:40:57,488 --> 00:40:59,255
YOU'RE GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT.

686
00:40:59,257 --> 00:41:00,390
THANK YOU.

687
00:41:00,392 --> 00:41:02,492
OKAY, LET'S GO FOR A HIKE!

688
00:41:02,494 --> 00:41:04,694
[ALL CHEER]

689
00:41:06,330 --> 00:41:08,898
[BEEPING]

690
00:41:12,503 --> 00:41:13,403
<i>[PHONE RINGING]</i>

691
00:41:13,405 --> 00:41:15,271
<i>YOU'VE REACHED MEGHAN DOHERTY.</i>
<i>PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE.</i>

692
00:41:15,273 --> 00:41:17,707
<i>HOLA,</i> MEGHAN, YOU'VE BEEN
GONE FOR TWO DAYS NOW.

693
00:41:17,709 --> 00:41:19,943
WE ALL KNOW WHEN YOU'RE
WORKING ON A A BIG DEAL
YOU STOP COMMUNICATING,

694
00:41:19,945 --> 00:41:26,082
BUT YOU MISSED OUR WEEKLY
FACIAL APPOINTMENT TODAY,
AND THAT'S NOT LIKE YOU.

695
00:41:26,084 --> 00:41:29,953
OKAY, CALL ME. BYE.

696
00:41:32,823 --> 00:41:36,826
GROUP THREE, WE'RE HERE,
AND YOU MIGHT NOTICE

697
00:41:36,828 --> 00:41:39,596
THAT THERE ARE
NO TENNIS RACKETS. BUT,

698
00:41:39,598 --> 00:41:43,867
WE DO HAVE THESE.

699
00:41:43,869 --> 00:41:47,203
OH, NO.

700
00:41:47,205 --> 00:41:50,240
IT IS BAD ENOUGH
THAT WE HIKED TWO MILES,

701
00:41:50,242 --> 00:41:51,641
AND NOW YOU EXPECT US
TO WORK?

702
00:41:51,643 --> 00:41:54,344
COME ON. IT'LL BE FUN.
YOU'LL HAVE FUN.

703
00:41:54,346 --> 00:41:56,546
WE'RE GONNA
CLEAN THIS PLACE UP.

704
00:41:56,548 --> 00:41:57,680
WE'RE GONNA GET IT NICE
AND BEAUTIFUL.

705
00:41:57,682 --> 00:42:03,319
WHAT IS FUN ABOUT HIKING TWO
MILES TO CLEAN A TENNIS COURT?

706
00:42:03,654 --> 00:42:05,622
IT'S NOT ABOUT THE WORK.

707
00:42:05,624 --> 00:42:07,924
IT'S ABOUT US
WORKING TOGETHER
AS A TEAM.

708
00:42:07,926 --> 00:42:11,194
I CAN'T BELIEVE
WHAT I'M HEARING.

709
00:42:11,196 --> 00:42:14,430
IT'S LIKE YOU'RE BRAINWASHED.

710
00:42:14,432 --> 00:42:16,866
[GROANS]

711
00:42:19,703 --> 00:42:20,703
OKAY.

712
00:42:20,705 --> 00:42:21,437
WE'LL START ON THIS END,

713
00:42:21,439 --> 00:42:24,107
AND WE GOTTA
WORK OUR WAY BACK.

714
00:42:24,109 --> 00:42:26,209
LET'S DO IT!

715
00:42:55,739 --> 00:42:58,241
HEY, MEGHAN.
EVERYTHING OKAY?

716
00:42:58,243 --> 00:43:00,877
NO. WHAT DO KIDS LEARN
FROM HIKING TWO MILES

717
00:43:00,879 --> 00:43:02,478
UP TO A TENNIS COURT
COVERED IN WEEDS,

718
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:06,716
AND GUESS WHAT? HERE ARE SOME
GLOVES AND SHOVELS AND LET'S
CLEAN THE TENNIS COURT

719
00:43:06,718 --> 00:43:09,285
AND LEARN ABOUT
THE GOOD LORD.
HMMM.

720
00:43:09,287 --> 00:43:12,956
- CALM DOWN.
- I AM NOT     GOING TO
CALM DOWN!

721
00:43:12,958 --> 00:43:15,725
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
SIGN THIS DOCUMENT?

722
00:43:15,727 --> 00:43:16,426
JUST GIVE UP ALREADY.

723
00:43:16,428 --> 00:43:18,962
THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN DO
TO SAVE THIS LAND.

724
00:43:18,964 --> 00:43:22,098
I GET IT THAT YOU ARE A MAN OF
GOD AND YOU LIVE OFF THIS AND,

725
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:25,368
BUT I DON'T SEE
A MIRACLE THAT'S GONNA
COME OUT OF THE SKY

726
00:43:25,370 --> 00:43:27,637
AND SAVE THIS PLACE!

727
00:43:27,639 --> 00:43:29,238
YOU DONE?

728
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,473
NO. DO YOU WANT
MORE MONEY?

729
00:43:30,475 --> 00:43:33,843
'CAUSE IF YOU WANT
MORE MONEY, I COULD
GET YOU MORE MONEY.

730
00:43:33,845 --> 00:43:35,511
WHAT IS IT THAT YOU WANT?

731
00:43:35,513 --> 00:43:36,646
MS. DOHERTY--

732
00:43:36,648 --> 00:43:37,947
WE HAVE AN AGREEMENT.

733
00:43:37,949 --> 00:43:40,516
I PLAN TO STICK TO MY END
IF YOU STICK TO YOURS.

734
00:43:40,518 --> 00:43:45,688
NOW IF YOU DON'T
GET BACK TO YOUR GROUP,
DEAL'S OFF.

735
00:43:53,497 --> 00:43:55,298
OH!

736
00:44:07,945 --> 00:44:11,314
WELL, WELCOME BACK!

737
00:44:19,990 --> 00:44:23,159
<i>[BLOW DRYER BLOWS, STOPS]</i>

738
00:44:24,928 --> 00:44:27,797
I NEED A FACIAL
AND A MAKEOVER SO BAD.

739
00:44:27,799 --> 00:44:30,667
WOW, YOU LOOK SO
DIFFERENT.

740
00:44:30,669 --> 00:44:33,169
YOU LOOK REALLY PRETTY
WITHOUT MAKEUP.

741
00:44:33,171 --> 00:44:34,137
[GROANS]

742
00:44:34,139 --> 00:44:39,709
OH, MY BODY HURTS SO BAD.

743
00:44:40,711 --> 00:44:43,413
HAVE YOU EVER HAD A FACIAL
OR--?

744
00:44:43,415 --> 00:44:46,249
[LAUGHS] NO.
NO.

745
00:44:46,251 --> 00:44:48,718
SIT RIGHT THERE.

746
00:44:51,755 --> 00:44:54,424
'KAY.

747
00:44:57,194 --> 00:45:00,863
YOU HAVE PRETTY HEALTHY SKIN.
YOU SHOULD TAKE CARE OF IT.

748
00:45:00,865 --> 00:45:02,465
OH, I WASH IT WITH SOAP.

749
00:45:02,467 --> 00:45:04,333
SOAP?

750
00:45:04,335 --> 00:45:07,470
SOAP IS THE HARSHEST THING
ON A LADY'S SKIN. HUH-UH.

751
00:45:07,472 --> 00:45:14,410
MY FRIEND VALENTINA AND I,
WE GET A FACIAL ONCE A WEEK.

752
00:45:14,412 --> 00:45:15,912
OH.

753
00:45:15,914 --> 00:45:20,416
I FEEL LIKE MY
FACE IS CRACKING.

754
00:45:24,154 --> 00:45:25,855
WANT TO SEE?

755
00:45:26,657 --> 00:45:30,226
[GIGGLES]

756
00:45:38,635 --> 00:45:42,405
<i>[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]</i>

757
00:45:42,407 --> 00:45:45,341
GOOD MORNING!

758
00:45:45,676 --> 00:45:48,377
[GROANS]
WHAT TIME IS IT?

759
00:45:48,379 --> 00:45:50,813
5:45.

760
00:45:50,815 --> 00:45:52,115
[GROANS]

761
00:45:52,117 --> 00:45:53,216
WHY DO WE HAVE TO GET UP
SO EARLY?

762
00:45:53,218 --> 00:45:58,321
"EARLY TO BED, EARLY TO RISE,
MAKES A GIRL HEALTHY, WEALTHY,
AND WISE."

763
00:45:58,323 --> 00:46:00,056
ALL RIGHT, I KNOW THAT'S
NOT IN THE BIBLE.

764
00:46:00,058 --> 00:46:05,194
HOW DID YOU SLEEP? GOSH,
LAST NIGHT WAS SO SPECIAL.

765
00:46:05,196 --> 00:46:09,632
JUST, IT WAS LIKE ALMOST
LIKE I HAD A SISTER.

766
00:46:12,436 --> 00:46:13,936
OW!

767
00:46:13,938 --> 00:46:14,704
ARE YOU OKAY?

768
00:46:14,706 --> 00:46:17,940
IT FEELS LIKE SOMEONE'S
POURED CONCRETE DOWN MY BACK.

769
00:46:17,942 --> 00:46:20,843
- OH NO!
- LISTEN, WHY DON'T
YOU JUST GO AHEAD

770
00:46:20,845 --> 00:46:27,049
AND TELL MR. GRAHAM
THAT I CAN'T GET OUT OF BED
BECAUSE MY BACK HURTS.

771
00:46:27,051 --> 00:46:29,485
JUST GO AHEAD.
[GROANS]

772
00:46:29,487 --> 00:46:32,288
[GROANING]

773
00:46:33,690 --> 00:46:35,825
<i>[DOOR SHUTS]</i>

774
00:47:04,288 --> 00:47:06,222
<i>HELLO, MEGHAN?</i>

775
00:47:06,390 --> 00:47:11,360
MY DAD ASKED ME
TO COME CHECK ON YOU.

776
00:47:12,329 --> 00:47:18,134
[KNOCKING]
MEGHAN, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

777
00:47:20,237 --> 00:47:22,772
I'M GONNA COME IN.
ARE YOU DRESSED?

778
00:47:22,774 --> 00:47:26,442
OW! OW!

779
00:47:27,377 --> 00:47:29,445
OW! [GROANS]

780
00:47:29,447 --> 00:47:30,413
ARE YOU OKAY?

781
00:47:30,415 --> 00:47:32,548
OH, I'M ALL RIGHT.

782
00:47:32,550 --> 00:47:35,284
I JUST STRAINED MY BACK
FROM PULLING WEEDS YESTERDAY.

783
00:47:35,286 --> 00:47:37,253
I THOUGHT I HAD SOME
IBUPROFEN IN THE CAR.

784
00:47:37,255 --> 00:47:38,421
WELL COME ON, LET'S
GET YOU SOME ASPIRIN.

785
00:47:38,423 --> 00:47:43,092
YOU WOULDN'T HAPPEN TO KNOW
WHERE THERE WOULD BE A PHONE
I COULD USE.

786
00:47:43,094 --> 00:47:46,028
YEAH, WELL, THE ONLY PHONE'S
IN MY FATHER'S OFFICE.

787
00:47:46,030 --> 00:47:50,600
OTHER THAN THAT THE CLOSEST
PHONE'S ABOUT 10 MILES AWAY
IN THE NEAREST TOWN.

788
00:47:50,602 --> 00:47:52,401
I COULD ASK HIM IF YOU LIKE.

789
00:47:52,403 --> 00:47:53,002
OH. OH, NO.

790
00:47:53,004 --> 00:47:56,172
I GUESS I COULD DRIVE
YOU TO TOWN IF IT'S
THAT IMPORTANT.

791
00:47:56,174 --> 00:47:58,040
YES, IT IS THAT IMPORTANT.

792
00:47:58,042 --> 00:47:59,141
JUST FAR ENOUGH UNTIL
I GET SOME CELL SIGNAL,

793
00:47:59,143 --> 00:48:01,544
- AND THEN I COULD
MAKE THE CALL.
- YEAH, SURE.

794
00:48:01,546 --> 00:48:05,481
COME ON. WE'LL TAKE MY CAR
AND WE'LL BE
BACK BEFORE LUNCH.

795
00:48:05,483 --> 00:48:07,683
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

796
00:48:08,385 --> 00:48:09,785
[GROANS]

797
00:48:28,071 --> 00:48:28,838
WHERE ARE
YOU GUYS HEADED?

798
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:32,208
SHE NEEDED TO MAKE
AN IMPORTANT CALL
AND USE THE PHONE.

799
00:48:32,210 --> 00:48:34,510
I DIDN'T WANT TO BOTHER YOU.

800
00:48:34,512 --> 00:48:37,546
IS THAT RIGHT, MEGHAN?

801
00:48:37,548 --> 00:48:38,814
YEAH.

802
00:48:38,816 --> 00:48:41,183
THAT'S RIGHT.

803
00:48:48,425 --> 00:48:49,492
YOU OKAY?
[SIGHS]

804
00:48:49,494 --> 00:48:53,329
YEAH. ALL OF A SUDDEN
I JUST FEEL SICK.

805
00:48:53,730 --> 00:48:56,799
MAYBE CAROL CAN HELP YOU
WITH HER SUDDEN SICKNESS.

806
00:48:56,801 --> 00:48:59,302
YOU KNOW, I THINK
I'LL BE OKAY.

807
00:48:59,304 --> 00:49:02,705
I JUST NEED TO
SIT DOWN AND REST.

808
00:49:17,054 --> 00:49:19,455
RUN! RUN!

809
00:49:19,457 --> 00:49:22,858
[ALL CHEERING, ROOTING]

810
00:49:35,105 --> 00:49:37,940
WE WOULD HAVE WON
IF I DIDN'T HAVE TO RUN
TWO LEGS OF THE RACE.

811
00:49:37,942 --> 00:49:42,678
YEAH, WHAT'S HER PROBLEM?
SHE SCARED OF BREAKING A NAIL?

812
00:49:49,619 --> 00:49:50,686
SO HOW DO YOU FEEL?

813
00:49:50,688 --> 00:49:53,255
I STILL FEEL A LITTLE DIZZY.

814
00:49:53,257 --> 00:49:55,291
I UNDERSTAND IF YOU
WANT TO LEAVE, BUT--

815
00:49:55,293 --> 00:49:56,892
I WASN'T TRYING TO LEAVE.

816
00:49:56,894 --> 00:49:59,261
I WILL BE HERE
UNTIL NEXT SATURDAY,

817
00:49:59,263 --> 00:50:01,230
'CAUSE WE AGREED
THAT YOU WOULD SIGN THAT DEED.

818
00:50:01,232 --> 00:50:03,599
AND I'LL BE HERE TO
PERSONALLY HAND IT TO YOU.

819
00:50:03,601 --> 00:50:05,468
IT SURE LOOKED LIKE YOU
WERE TRYING TO LEAVE TODAY.

820
00:50:05,470 --> 00:50:08,771
I WASN'T TRYING TO LEAVE.
I WAS MAKING A CALL.

821
00:50:08,773 --> 00:50:12,274
A JOB IS AT STAKE
AND I NEEDED TO LET
MR. WHITAKER KNOW

822
00:50:12,276 --> 00:50:13,676
IT'S TAKING A LOT LONGER
THAN I THOUGHT.

823
00:50:13,678 --> 00:50:18,447
MEGHAN, THE POINT IS
TO LEAVE THAT BEHIND.

824
00:50:18,449 --> 00:50:20,616
YOU BEING HERE
IS ABOUT RESTING

825
00:50:20,618 --> 00:50:22,418
AND GETTING IN TOUCH
WITH GOD.

826
00:50:22,420 --> 00:50:24,720
CALLING WHITAKER
IS NOT GONNA CHANGE THAT

827
00:50:24,722 --> 00:50:26,188
OR SPEED UP THE PROCESS.

828
00:50:26,190 --> 00:50:28,724
YOU ARE JUST SO IN CONTROL.

829
00:50:28,726 --> 00:50:30,092
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT I'VE
FIGURED OUT?

830
00:50:30,094 --> 00:50:35,031
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE WHO KNOWS
HOW BAD THINGS
ARE AROUND HERE.

831
00:50:35,033 --> 00:50:41,570
AND YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO KNOWS THAT THIS MAY BE
THE LAST WEEK

832
00:50:41,572 --> 00:50:43,472
THIS PLACE IS IN BUSINESS.

833
00:50:43,474 --> 00:50:47,910
I WONDER HOW YOUR FAMILY
WOULD FEEL IF THEY FOUND OUT.

834
00:50:50,180 --> 00:50:52,548
YOU THREATENING ME?

835
00:51:00,257 --> 00:51:06,328
<i>[PHONE RINGS]</i>
<i>YOU'VE REACHED MEGHAN DOHERTY.</i>
<i>PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE.</i>

836
00:51:06,330 --> 00:51:07,296
MEGHAN, HEY, IT'S ME.

837
00:51:07,298 --> 00:51:09,265
I'VE BEEN CALLING
FOR THREE DAYS NOW.

838
00:51:09,267 --> 00:51:11,667
NO ONE AT GOD'S COUNTRY
IS ANSWERING THE PHONE.

839
00:51:11,669 --> 00:51:17,006
SO, IF YOU HAD CLOSED
THE DEAL YOU WOULD HAVES
CALLED BY NOW, RIGHT?

840
00:51:17,008 --> 00:51:20,576
I'M REALLY GETTING WORRIED.

841
00:51:22,179 --> 00:51:23,679
<i>HOLA, MEGHAN,</i>
<i>SOY YO.</i>

842
00:51:23,681 --> 00:51:25,181
IT'S VALENTINA.

843
00:51:25,183 --> 00:51:27,883
I WISH YOU WOULD JUST
PICK UP THE PHONE.

844
00:51:27,885 --> 00:51:31,487
WE ARE ALL TRYING
TO LOCATE YOU.

845
00:51:31,489 --> 00:51:33,622
I REALLY HOPE THAT

846
00:51:33,624 --> 00:51:39,161
YOUR NOT CALLING HAS ANYTHING
TO DO WITH OUR DISCUSSION
THE OTHER NIGHT.

847
00:51:39,163 --> 00:51:41,630
I'M SO SORRY.

848
00:51:41,632 --> 00:51:45,134
I MISS YOU.

849
00:51:45,136 --> 00:51:48,771
PLEASE, JUST,
JUST CALL ME BACK OR,

850
00:51:48,773 --> 00:51:51,173
OR CALL ADAM, OKAY?

851
00:51:51,175 --> 00:51:53,209
ALL RIGHT.

852
00:51:53,211 --> 00:51:55,244
BYE.

853
00:51:58,181 --> 00:52:01,417
<i>[SINGING CAMPFIRE SONG]</i>

854
00:52:03,753 --> 00:52:08,190
<i>♪ GOTTA LOVE IT IN GOD'S</i>
<i>COUNTRY...  ♪</i>

855
00:52:21,638 --> 00:52:23,506
<i>NICE!</i>

856
00:52:23,508 --> 00:52:25,141
<i>[CLAPPING]</i>

857
00:52:25,143 --> 00:52:27,176
YOU KNOW WHAT, I WAS
JUST THINKING SOMETHING.

858
00:52:27,178 --> 00:52:31,547
WHEN I WAS A KID GROWING UP
IN CALIFORNIA,

859
00:52:31,549 --> 00:52:33,849
ONE OF THE THINGS
THAT I REMEMBER THE MOST

860
00:52:33,851 --> 00:52:37,153
WAS SPENDING THE HOLIDAYS
TOGETHER WITH MY FAMILY.

861
00:52:37,155 --> 00:52:38,888
AND EVEN THOUGH WE WERE
ALL PACKED IN THERE--

862
00:52:38,890 --> 00:52:41,223
IT WAS A TINY LITTLE
TWO-BEDROOM HOUSE--

863
00:52:41,225 --> 00:52:42,324
I WAS THE RUNT-

864
00:52:42,326 --> 00:52:43,259
RIGHTFULLY SO!

865
00:52:43,261 --> 00:52:44,160
I SLEPT ON THE FLOOR.

866
00:52:44,162 --> 00:52:47,096
I HAD MY BROTHER HERE,
I HAD MY SISTER HERE.

867
00:52:47,098 --> 00:52:49,598
COUSINS EVERYWHERE.

868
00:52:49,600 --> 00:52:52,535
I NEVER FELT CROWDED.

869
00:52:52,537 --> 00:52:54,403
NEVER.

870
00:52:54,405 --> 00:52:55,104
YOU KNOW WHAT I FELT?

871
00:52:55,106 --> 00:52:59,675
I FELT LOVE.
I FELT TOGETHERNESS.

872
00:52:59,677 --> 00:53:02,244
I JUST DON'T THINK THERE'S
ANYTHING THAT CAN REPLACE
THAT FEELING,

873
00:53:02,246 --> 00:53:08,384
THAT FEELING OF BEING
TOGETHER WITH YOUR FAMILY.

874
00:53:08,386 --> 00:53:09,518
AMEN.

875
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:09,952
AMEN.

876
00:53:09,954 --> 00:53:12,655
I THINK MAYBE WE SHOULD
TAKE A LITTLE MOMENT HERE

877
00:53:12,657 --> 00:53:15,090
TO REALIZE HOW LUCKY WE ARE

878
00:53:15,092 --> 00:53:19,695
TO BE HERE WITH EACH OTHER.

879
00:53:21,097 --> 00:53:23,532
<i>AMEN.</i>

880
00:53:24,968 --> 00:53:26,435
ALL RIGHT.

881
00:53:26,437 --> 00:53:27,469
[CAMPFIRE SONG CONTINUES]

882
00:53:27,471 --> 00:53:30,673
<i>[PEOPLE TALKING, LAUGHING]</i>

883
00:53:33,043 --> 00:53:37,313
I'M SORRY IF I GOT YOU
INTO ANY TROUBLE THIS MORNING.

884
00:53:37,315 --> 00:53:42,318
NO, YOU DIDN'T GET ME
INTO ANY TROUBLE.

885
00:53:42,320 --> 00:53:44,587
I DO HAVE A QUESTION
FOR YOU.

886
00:53:44,589 --> 00:53:48,624
WHAT'S GOING ON? WHY IS
MY FATHER
HOVERING OVER YOU LIKE

887
00:53:48,626 --> 00:53:50,859
MOTHER OVER A NEW BORN BABY?

888
00:53:54,798 --> 00:53:59,001
WHEN I CAME HERE I TOLD
HIM THAT I NEEDED HELP.

889
00:53:59,003 --> 00:54:03,105
AND SO HE AGREED TO HELP ME
AND TREAT ME LIKE EVERYONE
ELSE.

890
00:54:03,107 --> 00:54:07,443
I'M NOT BEING NOSY,
BUT HELP YOU WITH WHAT?

891
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:11,614
DON'T WORRY. I'M NOT
A DRUG ADDICT OR ANYTHING.

892
00:54:11,616 --> 00:54:13,949
I'M A WORKAHOLIC.

893
00:54:13,951 --> 00:54:18,020
AND SO IT'S WORK THAT
I THINK ABOUT ALL THE TIME

894
00:54:18,022 --> 00:54:21,023
AND HENCE I'M
UP HERE FOR REST.

895
00:54:21,025 --> 00:54:24,360
HENCE, NO CELL PHONES,
NO COMPUTERS,

896
00:54:24,362 --> 00:54:25,527
NONE OF THAT STUFF.

897
00:54:25,529 --> 00:54:27,463
THAT'S WHAT YOUR DAD'S
BEEN HELPING ME WITH.

898
00:54:27,465 --> 00:54:32,301
YEAH, WELL, HE CAN BE
BULLHEADED AND STUBBORN
SOMETIMES.

899
00:54:32,402 --> 00:54:35,170
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

900
00:54:37,440 --> 00:54:39,608
HOW'S YOUR BACK?

901
00:54:41,678 --> 00:54:43,679
YOU KNOW, IT'S--

902
00:54:43,681 --> 00:54:45,681
IT'S STILL A LITTLE TIGHT

903
00:54:45,683 --> 00:54:50,452
BUT I THINK THE ASPIRIN
HAS HELPED EASE THE PAIN.

904
00:54:54,658 --> 00:54:56,125
[BOTH]
SO WHAT DO YOU--

905
00:54:56,127 --> 00:54:58,027
[BOTH LAUGH]

906
00:54:58,029 --> 00:54:58,994
SO TELL ME ABOUT JAKE.

907
00:54:58,996 --> 00:55:03,065
I'VE BEEN A COUNSELOR HERE
SINCE MY PARENTS OWN AND
RUN THE PLACE.

908
00:55:03,067 --> 00:55:06,568
I LEFT FOR A COUPLE
OF YEARS TO GO TO
COLLEGE AND BUSINESS SCHOOL

909
00:55:06,570 --> 00:55:09,972
AND THEN I CAME BACK
TO HELP MY MOTHER AND
FATHER RUN IT.

910
00:55:09,974 --> 00:55:12,808
WHERE DID YOU GO
TO BUSINESS SCHOOL?

911
00:55:12,810 --> 00:55:15,411
HARVARD.

912
00:55:15,779 --> 00:55:19,515
YOU WENT TO HARVARD
BUSINESS SCHOOL?

913
00:55:19,517 --> 00:55:20,783
YEAH.

914
00:55:20,785 --> 00:55:22,217
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE

915
00:55:22,219 --> 00:55:23,018
WORKING AS A COUNSELOR?

916
00:55:23,020 --> 00:55:28,590
WHO NEEDS WALL STREET? I CAME
HERE TO LEARN HOW TO BUILD
THE PERFECT BONFIRE.

917
00:55:28,592 --> 00:55:33,295
PLUS I MAKE
ONE HECK OF A SMORE.

918
00:55:39,869 --> 00:55:42,037
LISTEN, DO YOU
WANT TO COME WITH ME?

919
00:55:42,039 --> 00:55:44,840
THERE'S SOMETHING
I WANT TO SHOW YOU.

920
00:55:46,276 --> 00:55:48,410
OKAY.

921
00:55:48,945 --> 00:55:52,281
SO, THIS IS MY VISION.

922
00:55:52,283 --> 00:55:54,616
I WANT TO BUILD
A CHRISTIAN COLLEGE WITH
FULL STUDENT HOUSING.

923
00:55:54,618 --> 00:55:59,988
THE CAMPUS WILL BE A STATE
OF THE ART COLLEGE WITH
FULL ACADEMIC CURRICULUM.

924
00:55:59,990 --> 00:56:01,290
AND THE STUDENTS, THEY
CAN EARN COLLEGE CREDIT

925
00:56:01,292 --> 00:56:03,892
AND THEY CAN EARN SCHOLARSHIPS
BY WORKING AT THE CAMP
DURING THE SUMMER.

926
00:56:03,894 --> 00:56:11,200
THIS IS A DAY CARE CENTER
FOR SINGLE MOTHERS THAT
WANT TO ATTEND THE COLLEGE.

927
00:56:11,202 --> 00:56:14,136
THIS IS STUDENT HOUSING,
AND LOOK AT THIS.

928
00:56:14,138 --> 00:56:17,773
THAT'S THE STUDENT ACTIVITY
CENTER.

929
00:56:17,775 --> 00:56:21,243
I'M IMPRESSED.
DOES YOUR FATHER
KNOW ABOUT THIS?

930
00:56:21,245 --> 00:56:22,811
YEAH, OF COURSE HE DOES.
WE SPENT THOUSANDS

931
00:56:22,813 --> 00:56:26,248
PUTTING TOGETHER
A BUSINESS PLAN WITH
SOME REALLY SOLID PROJECTIONS.

932
00:56:26,250 --> 00:56:28,517
AND WE CAN GET STATE FUNDING,
TAX RELIEF.

933
00:56:28,519 --> 00:56:31,687
I'M TALKING ABOUT BUILDING
AN ENTIRE INFRASTRUCTURE HERE,

934
00:56:31,689 --> 00:56:37,726
I MEAN ELECTRICITY, SEWAGE,
WATER, PAVING A ROAD THAT GOES
ALL THE WAY TO THE HIGHWAY.

935
00:56:37,728 --> 00:56:40,229
I'M SORRY. AM I BORING YOU
WITH THIS?

936
00:56:40,231 --> 00:56:40,629
NO! NO.

937
00:56:40,631 --> 00:56:43,699
SO WHY HAVEN'T YOU
PUT THIS PLAN INTO ACTION?

938
00:56:43,701 --> 00:56:46,735
GRAHAM ESTATES IS
A NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION.

939
00:56:46,737 --> 00:56:48,971
IT RAISES MOST OF OUR MONEY
THROUGH CHURCH OFFERINGS.

940
00:56:48,973 --> 00:56:52,408
WITH THE ECONOMY HITTING
ALL CHURCHES, BIG AND SMALL,

941
00:56:52,410 --> 00:56:54,943
IT'S PUT OUR ENTIRE
ORGANIZATION INTO FLUX.

942
00:56:54,945 --> 00:56:57,479
WHAT WE NEED IS
A VENTURE CAPITALIST
TO INVEST,

943
00:56:57,481 --> 00:57:00,482
BUT SO FAR EFFORTS
HAVE FALLEN ON DEAF EARS.

944
00:57:00,484 --> 00:57:05,587
OUR VISION IS
NOT THEIR VISION.
MY FAMILY--

945
00:57:05,589 --> 00:57:09,858
WE REALLY BELIEVE IN HELPING
THOSE WHO NEED HELP.

946
00:57:09,860 --> 00:57:12,494
IT'S GOD'S WAY.

947
00:57:16,866 --> 00:57:18,767
<i>[HOSHI YAKAMOTO]</i>
<i>PAPERWORK LOOKS GOOD.</i>

948
00:57:18,769 --> 00:57:21,003
<i>WE ARE READY TO MOVE FORWARD</i>
<i>WITH WHITAKER AND ASSOCIATES.</i>

949
00:57:21,005 --> 00:57:24,907
<i>MR. WHITAKER, ONE QUESTION--</i>
<i>WHERE'S MS. DOHERTY?</i>

950
00:57:24,909 --> 00:57:25,808
HAVE YOU HEARD ANYTHING?

951
00:57:25,810 --> 00:57:26,675
NOTHING. ADAM, I'M WORRIED.

952
00:57:26,677 --> 00:57:30,212
<i>- MY BROTHER THINKS</i>
<i>SHE'S VERY IMPRESSIVE.</i>
<i>-</i> [PHONE RINGS]

953
00:57:30,214 --> 00:57:31,814
IT'S BEEN FOUR DAYS!

954
00:57:31,816 --> 00:57:32,881
OKAY, HOLD ON.

955
00:57:32,883 --> 00:57:34,750
YES.
MS. DOHERTY?

956
00:57:34,752 --> 00:57:36,718
VALENTINA HASN'T
HEARD ANYTHING.

957
00:57:36,720 --> 00:57:39,021
...AND SHE IS. SHE IS
VERY IMPRESSIVE INDEED,

958
00:57:39,023 --> 00:57:43,325
- AND RIGHT NOW SHE'S AWAY.
SHE'S HANDLING...
- UH--

959
00:57:43,327 --> 00:57:44,993
...SOME VERY DETAILED
BUSINESS...

960
00:57:44,995 --> 00:57:46,728
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO
OR HOW TO REACH HER.

961
00:57:46,730 --> 00:57:50,432
WHY DOESN'T SOMEONE JUST
DRIVE DOWN THERE AND MAKE
SURE SHE'S ALL RIGHT?

962
00:57:50,434 --> 00:57:54,970
- UH...
- ...I CAN ASSURE YOU THAT
EVERYTHING IS GOING TO PLAN,

963
00:57:54,972 --> 00:57:59,408
AND THE CLOSING WILL
TAKE PLACE ON TIME.

964
00:57:59,410 --> 00:58:00,809
HOW'S THE WEATHER
OVER THERE, HOSHI?

965
00:58:00,811 --> 00:58:04,980
MR. WHITAKER DOESN'T WANT
TO GO DOWN AND INTERFERE.

966
00:58:04,982 --> 00:58:06,982
HE'D PREFER FOR MEGHAN
TO CALL IN.

967
00:58:06,984 --> 00:58:09,218
SHE'S WORKING ON SOME
REALLY BIG DEAL FOR THE FIRM.

968
00:58:09,220 --> 00:58:13,322
I DON'T KNOW MUCH ABOUT IT,
THOUGH, OTHER THAN IT'S
WORTH A LOT OF MONEY.

969
00:58:13,324 --> 00:58:15,891
FORGET WHITAKER AND HOW MUCH
MONEY THIS DEAL IS WORTH.

970
00:58:15,893 --> 00:58:18,694
WHAT IF SHE'S IN TROUBLE?
WHAT IF SHE NEEDS OUR HELP?

971
00:58:18,696 --> 00:58:20,629
- UH--
-  <i>ANYTHING COULD HAVE</i>
<i>HAPPENED TO HER.</i>

972
00:58:20,631 --> 00:58:24,233
YOU GET ON THAT PHONE
AND CALL THE STATE POLICE

973
00:58:24,235 --> 00:58:26,835
AND PLACE A MISSING PERSONS
REPORT.

974
00:58:26,837 --> 00:58:29,972
DON'T JUST SIT AROUND
AND DO NOTHING.
YOU HEAR ME?

975
00:58:29,974 --> 00:58:34,042
OKAY, WELL, LOOK, MR. WHITAKER
SAYS IF SHE DOESN'T CALL IN
THE NEXT COUPLE OF DAYS,

976
00:58:34,044 --> 00:58:39,548
HE'LL GO DOWN THERE HIMSELF.
ALL RIGHT? I GOTTA GO, THOUGH.
OKAY, BYE.

977
00:58:39,550 --> 00:58:42,484
YOU CAN'T KEEP
PUTTING THIS OFF.
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?

978
00:58:42,486 --> 00:58:48,690
I DON'T KNOW. WE'VE TRIED
HER CELL MANY TIMES.
THERE'S NO ANSWER.

979
00:58:48,692 --> 00:58:50,192
ADAM, OUR FRIEND IS MISSING.

980
00:58:50,194 --> 00:58:53,061
IF YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO CALL 911, I WILL.

981
00:58:53,063 --> 00:58:54,563
YOU DECIDE.

982
00:58:54,565 --> 00:58:56,865
IF I CALL 911 AND SHE'S OKAY,

983
00:58:56,867 --> 00:59:00,602
I RISK BLOWING HER DEAL
AND MY JOB.

984
00:59:03,606 --> 00:59:06,275
[CHEERING, CLAPPING]

985
00:59:14,551 --> 00:59:16,218
HOW'S YOUR BACK?

986
00:59:16,220 --> 00:59:16,919
MY BACK'S DOING GOOD.

987
00:59:16,921 --> 00:59:19,721
HEY, MEGHAN, I COULD
USE YOUR HELP ON THIS PULL.

988
00:59:19,723 --> 00:59:20,856
NO!

989
00:59:20,858 --> 00:59:21,757
COME ON!

990
00:59:21,759 --> 00:59:23,458
YOU CAN DO IT.

991
00:59:23,460 --> 00:59:25,060
[CLAPPING]

992
00:59:25,062 --> 00:59:26,228
MEGHAN!

993
00:59:26,230 --> 00:59:28,397
MEGHAN! MEGHAN!

994
00:59:28,399 --> 00:59:31,099
OH, WAIT A SECOND.
LET ME PUT MY HAIR UP.

995
00:59:31,101 --> 00:59:32,434
BRING IT ON, BLONDIE!

996
00:59:32,436 --> 00:59:33,702
YOU'RE GOIN' DOWN!

997
00:59:33,704 --> 00:59:36,071
YOU'RE GOIN' DOWN.
YOU GOT NOTHING.

998
00:59:36,073 --> 00:59:38,540
<i>[ADAM] GRAB YOUR ROPES,</i>
<i>EVERYBODY!</i>

999
00:59:38,542 --> 00:59:41,276
<i>ON YOUR MARKS,</i>

1000
00:59:41,278 --> 00:59:43,612
GET SET,

1001
00:59:43,614 --> 00:59:44,846
PULL!

1002
00:59:44,848 --> 00:59:46,114
[SQUEALS]

1003
00:59:46,116 --> 00:59:48,417
<i>[JAKE] BRING IT ON!</i>

1004
00:59:48,718 --> 00:59:52,254
OKAY, COME ON, COME ON!
ONE, TWO THREE!

1005
00:59:52,256 --> 00:59:53,655
COME ON, GUYS!
PULL!

1006
00:59:53,657 --> 00:59:55,223
ONE, TWO THREE! PULL!

1007
00:59:55,225 --> 00:59:56,191
PULL HARDER!

1008
00:59:56,193 --> 00:59:58,160
COME ON GUYS!
HERE WE GO!

1009
00:59:58,162 --> 01:00:01,263
ONE, TWO THREE! PULL!

1010
01:00:08,571 --> 01:00:10,839
YOU DID
A GREAT JOB!

1011
01:00:14,510 --> 01:00:18,447
MEGHAN, HE HAS NEVER LOST!
THAT IS AMAZING!

1012
01:00:18,449 --> 01:00:23,552
VICTORY, BABY!
VICTORY!

1013
01:00:27,523 --> 01:00:29,524
GREAT JOB.

1014
01:00:30,627 --> 01:00:32,494
SO THIS IS IT.

1015
01:00:32,496 --> 01:00:34,630
THIS IS WHAT IT'S ALL ABOUT.

1016
01:00:34,632 --> 01:00:36,898
WOW.

1017
01:00:36,900 --> 01:00:40,102
<i>THIS IS YOUR REWARD</i>
<i>FOR WINNING AT TUG-OF-WAR.</i>

1018
01:00:40,104 --> 01:00:42,204
<i>[MEGHAN] YOU DIDN'T</i>
<i>LET ME WIN, DID YOU?</i>

1019
01:00:42,206 --> 01:00:48,343
<i>TRUST ME WHEN I TELL YOU THIS.</i>
<i>I LOVE TO WIN TOO MUCH</i>
<i>TO ALLOW YOU TO WIN.</i>

1020
01:01:02,458 --> 01:01:05,694
OKAY, I-- I HAVE TO GO.
[TO HERSELF] STAY ON TASK...

1021
01:01:05,696 --> 01:01:08,463
- WAIT.
- ...IT'S NOT PERSONAL.
IT'S BUSINESS...

1022
01:01:08,465 --> 01:01:10,098
DID I DO SOMETHING WRONG?

1023
01:01:10,100 --> 01:01:13,568
CAN YOU TAKE ME BACK
TO CAMP?

1024
01:01:15,471 --> 01:01:19,341
MEGHAN, SO,
I SPOKE TO A GUY

1025
01:01:19,343 --> 01:01:20,042
OUT AT GOD'S COUNTRY,

1026
01:01:20,044 --> 01:01:23,779
AND HE SAID THAT A MEGHAN
DOUBTFIRE WITH A FERRARI

1027
01:01:23,781 --> 01:01:26,848
HAS BEEN OUT THERE
FOR THE PAST FIVE DAYS.

1028
01:01:26,850 --> 01:01:29,785
SO WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

1029
01:01:29,787 --> 01:01:31,787
WHAT HAVE THEY DONE TO YOU?

1030
01:01:31,789 --> 01:01:34,089
LOOK, I DON'T CARE
ABOUT THE YAKAMOTO DEAL.

1031
01:01:34,091 --> 01:01:38,226
BUT IF I DON'T HEAR FROM YOU
BY THE END OF THE AUCTION,

1032
01:01:38,228 --> 01:01:39,127
I'M CALLING THE POLICE.

1033
01:01:39,129 --> 01:01:40,829
SO WHAT DO YOU DO
FOR A LIVING?

1034
01:01:40,831 --> 01:01:46,568
- I'M IN REAL ESTATE.
- OH, REAL ESTATE.
THAT SOUNDS INTERESTING.

1035
01:01:46,570 --> 01:01:47,402
I WANT TO MAJOR
IN CIVIL LAW.

1036
01:01:47,404 --> 01:01:51,173
MY FATHER'S A LAWYER, SO
I GET TO SEE HOW HE HELPS
PEOPLE OUT OF TIGHT SPOTS.

1037
01:01:51,175 --> 01:01:55,577
I CAN NEVER SEE YOU
AS A PERSON WHO WOULD
MAJOR IN LAW.

1038
01:01:55,579 --> 01:02:02,150
WHY, 'CAUSE I'M NOT
ALL GLAMOROUS LIKE YOU?

1039
01:02:02,152 --> 01:02:04,419
I ALWAYS WANTED TO FIT IN
WITH THE GIRLS, YOU KNOW.

1040
01:02:04,421 --> 01:02:06,955
IT'S JUST, I HAVE
FOUR BROTHERS.

1041
01:02:06,957 --> 01:02:09,391
IT'S JUST EASIER
TO PLAY ROUGH, YOU NOW?

1042
01:02:09,393 --> 01:02:14,262
I HAVE AN IDEA. LISTEN,
WHY DON'T YOU COME
TO LOS ANGELES

1043
01:02:14,264 --> 01:02:16,198
FOR A WEEKEND WITH ME?

1044
01:02:16,200 --> 01:02:16,598
REALLY?

1045
01:02:16,600 --> 01:02:21,470
YEAH, WE CAN,
WE CAN GO SHOPPING,

1046
01:02:21,472 --> 01:02:22,838
AND--

1047
01:02:22,840 --> 01:02:29,845
WE COULD FIND YOU A NEW
HAIR STYLE.

1048
01:02:32,682 --> 01:02:35,684
HOW DOES THAT SOUND?
WE COULD HAVE SOME GIRL TIME?

1049
01:02:35,686 --> 01:02:37,886
YOU KNOW, JUST DO
A BUNCH OF GIRL THINGS.

1050
01:02:37,888 --> 01:02:39,721
I WOULD LIKE THAT.

1051
01:02:39,723 --> 01:02:40,455
YEAH?

1052
01:02:40,457 --> 01:02:41,656
SOUNDS LIKE
SOMETHING MY MOTHER

1053
01:02:41,658 --> 01:02:43,258
AND I WOULD
HAVE DONE TOGETHER.

1054
01:02:43,260 --> 01:02:44,626
OH. WHERE'S YOUR MOTHER?

1055
01:02:44,628 --> 01:02:47,395
SHE DIED LAST YEAR.

1056
01:02:48,431 --> 01:02:50,465
I'M SORRY.

1057
01:02:50,467 --> 01:02:55,170
MY FATHER DIED WHEN
I WAS ABOUT YOUR AGE.

1058
01:02:55,172 --> 01:02:57,806
I DID EVERYTHING
WITH HIM, AND THEN

1059
01:02:57,808 --> 01:03:00,208
WHEN HE DIED I JUST LOST
INTEREST IN EVERYTHING.

1060
01:03:00,210 --> 01:03:06,181
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT? YOU SEEM
TOO NICE TO BE A LAWYER.

1061
01:03:06,183 --> 01:03:08,450
ALL THE LAWYERS I KNOW
ARE JUST RUTHLESS.

1062
01:03:08,452 --> 01:03:11,186
THERE'S GOOD AND BAD IN
EVERYTHING AND EVERYONE.

1063
01:03:11,188 --> 01:03:12,921
I WANT TO BE A LAWYER
SO I CAN--

1064
01:03:12,923 --> 01:03:17,692
SO I CAN FIGHT FOR
THE PEOPLE THAT CAN'T AFFORD
TO FIGHT FOR THEMSELVES.

1065
01:03:17,694 --> 01:03:18,760
YOU KNOW, FOR EXAMPLE,

1066
01:03:18,762 --> 01:03:21,630
SAY THERE'S THIS BIG BANK
THAT LOCKS AN ELDERLY COUPLE
INTO A BAD MORTGAGE,

1067
01:03:21,632 --> 01:03:27,169
AND THEN TRIES TO EVICT THEM
FROM THEIR HOME FOR THE MONEY
'CAUSE THEY'RE GREEDY.

1068
01:03:27,171 --> 01:03:29,371
THAT'S WHEN I WOULD SWOOP IN--
SUPERLAWYER EXTRAORDINAIRE,

1069
01:03:29,373 --> 01:03:34,209
COMING IN, SAVING THE DAY,
SAVING THE ELDERLY COUPLE,

1070
01:03:34,211 --> 01:03:36,511
PUNISHES THE BANK,
DOES THE RIGHT THING,

1071
01:03:36,513 --> 01:03:39,447
I DON'T KNOW, I THINK
IT'D BE GREAT.

1072
01:03:56,232 --> 01:04:00,969
<i>[GERI] I KNOW THIS VERSE ON</i>
<i>GREED. ISAIAH 56:11.</i>

1073
01:04:00,971 --> 01:04:06,808
"YEAH, THEY ARE GREEDY DOGS
WHO CAN NEVER HAVE ENOUGH.

1074
01:04:06,810 --> 01:04:10,679
THEY ARE SHEPHERDS
THAT CAN NOT UNDERSTAND."

1075
01:04:17,386 --> 01:04:20,522
<i>[CELL PHONE RINGS]</i>

1076
01:04:25,127 --> 01:04:29,931
<i>[CELL PHONE RINGING]</i>

1077
01:05:09,739 --> 01:05:13,808
WHERE ARE YOU, MEGHAN?

1078
01:05:14,143 --> 01:05:18,280
THIS IS WHAT
I WAS TALKING ABOUT, JAKE.

1079
01:05:19,081 --> 01:05:21,549
LUKE 10:23.

1080
01:05:21,551 --> 01:05:23,251
<i>"BLESSED ARE THE EYES</i>
<i>THAT SEE WHAT YOU SEE."</i>

1081
01:05:23,253 --> 01:05:27,088
- HOW ARE YOU DOING
THIS MORNING?
- GREAT. GOOD TO SEE YOU.

1082
01:05:27,090 --> 01:05:29,190
<i>YEAH?</i>
HEY, JAKE.

1083
01:05:29,192 --> 01:05:30,125
THE TRUCK. WHERE IS IT?

1084
01:05:30,127 --> 01:05:31,159
<i>RIGHT IN FRONT OF THE OFFICE.</i>

1085
01:05:31,161 --> 01:05:32,994
<i>YUP.</i>
KEYS INSIDE?

1086
01:05:32,996 --> 01:05:34,963
THANKS, MAN.

1087
01:05:36,399 --> 01:05:39,401
<i>[EDEN] COME IN, MEGHAN.</i>

1088
01:05:39,502 --> 01:05:43,271
- EDEN?
- HI, MEGHAN.
HAVE A SEAT.

1089
01:05:43,273 --> 01:05:45,740
I HAVE A CONFESSION TO MAKE.

1090
01:05:45,742 --> 01:05:50,545
MR. WHITAKER DIDN'T SEND ME
DOWN HERE JUST
TO MAKE AN OFFER.

1091
01:05:50,547 --> 01:05:53,248
THERE'S A PAIR OF BUSINESSMEN,
THE YAKAMOTO BROTHERS,

1092
01:05:53,250 --> 01:05:54,983
AND THEY'RE HERE
TO DEVELOP THE LAND.

1093
01:05:54,985 --> 01:05:57,886
THEY WANT TO TURN IT
INTO A CASINO AND RESORT.

1094
01:05:57,888 --> 01:06:00,722
IT'S A $100 MILLION DEAL
AND I DON'T SEE ANY WAY

1095
01:06:00,724 --> 01:06:01,923
THAT YOU COULD STOP IT
FROM HAPPENING,

1096
01:06:01,925 --> 01:06:06,761
ESPECIALLY SINCE TOMORROW
IS THE AUCTION.

1097
01:06:06,763 --> 01:06:10,031
THANKS FOR
THE INFORMATION, MEGHAN.

1098
01:06:10,033 --> 01:06:13,335
THERE'S NOTHING LEFT
FOR ME TO DO BUT PRAY.

1099
01:06:13,337 --> 01:06:15,503
WILL YOU STOP IT?

1100
01:06:15,505 --> 01:06:17,539
RIGHT NOW IS THE DECISION!

1101
01:06:17,541 --> 01:06:18,873
MR.
WHITAKER IS GONNA COME DOWN

1102
01:06:18,875 --> 01:06:20,275
THE ROAD ANY
SECOND NOW AND JUST

1103
01:06:20,277 --> 01:06:22,777
SHUT DOWN
THE ENTIRE OPERATION,

1104
01:06:22,779 --> 01:06:25,413
INCLUDING ME.

1105
01:06:26,515 --> 01:06:27,949
I GET IT. I UNDERSTAND.

1106
01:06:27,951 --> 01:06:32,020
THERE IS SOMETHING REALLY
SPECIAL ABOUT THIS LAND.

1107
01:06:32,022 --> 01:06:34,322
BUT YOU HAVE TO BE PROACTIVE.

1108
01:06:34,324 --> 01:06:39,461
JAKE SHARED WITH ME THE ENTIRE
VISION YOU HAVE TO BUILD
A CHRISTIAN COLLEGE.

1109
01:06:39,463 --> 01:06:41,429
YOU'VE GOT TO FIND SOMEONE
TO INVEST IN IT,

1110
01:06:41,431 --> 01:06:45,166
TO PAY UP THE DEBT,
TO BUY THIS
LAND SO YOU CAN PUT THIS CAMP

1111
01:06:45,168 --> 01:06:48,603
I'VE TRIED EVERYTHING.
I'VE CALLED EVERYONE
I KNOW WITH MONEY

1112
01:06:48,605 --> 01:06:51,740
THAT COULD MAYBE BAIL ME OUT,
BUT SO FAR, NO ONE.

1113
01:06:51,742 --> 01:06:55,844
ALL I HAVE LEFT IS
MY FAITH IN GOD.

1114
01:06:56,312 --> 01:06:59,014
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND?
THAT'S ALL I HAVE LEFT.

1115
01:06:59,016 --> 01:07:02,984
BUT WHAT ABOUT JAKE
AND EVERYONE ELSE?

1116
01:07:04,186 --> 01:07:04,786
JAKE TRUSTS YOU.

1117
01:07:04,788 --> 01:07:11,359
HE TRUSTS THAT
YOU AND HIM ARE GONNA
COMPLETE THIS VISION.

1118
01:07:14,196 --> 01:07:20,902
YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU'RE RIGHT. YOU'RE RIGHT
ABOUT THE WHOLE SITUATION.

1119
01:07:21,203 --> 01:07:24,372
YEAH. YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M GONNA TELL MY FAMILY
TONIGHT.

1120
01:07:24,374 --> 01:07:28,443
IT'S NOT FAIR T HIDE THINGS
FROM THE ONES YOU LOVE.

1121
01:07:28,445 --> 01:07:30,245
IT'S JUST NOT FAIR.

1122
01:07:30,247 --> 01:07:31,379
THEY HAVE THE RIGHT TO KNOW.

1123
01:07:31,381 --> 01:07:32,680
OKAY.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

1124
01:07:32,682 --> 01:07:35,850
NO. I WANT YOU
TO COME WITH ME.

1125
01:07:41,157 --> 01:07:44,492
CAN I HAVE YOUR
ATTENTION, EVERYONE?

1126
01:07:50,332 --> 01:07:54,536
IN JOHN CHAPTER 8,
THE PASSAGE STATES,

1127
01:07:54,538 --> 01:07:59,441
"THEN YOU WILL KNOW
THE TRUTH, AND THE TRUTH
WILL SET YOU FREE."

1128
01:07:59,443 --> 01:08:04,813
WELL, I HAVE A CONFESSION TO
MAKE ABOUT GOD'S COUNTRY.

1129
01:08:04,815 --> 01:08:05,980
WE'RE IN FORECLOSURE.

1130
01:08:05,982 --> 01:08:08,216
<i>AND AS OF SATURDAY</i>
<i>WE WILL BE NO MORE.</i>

1131
01:08:08,218 --> 01:08:15,123
<i>THE LAND WILL GOT TO AUCTION</i>
<i>TO THE HIGHEST BIDDER.</i>

1132
01:08:15,125 --> 01:08:16,424
BUT THE GOOD NEWS IS,

1133
01:08:16,426 --> 01:08:17,959
THEY MADE US AN OFFER,
AND WITH THE MONEY,

1134
01:08:17,961 --> 01:08:19,994
<i>WE'LL BE ABLE TO</i>
<i>START OVER IN A NEW CITY.</i>

1135
01:08:19,996 --> 01:08:24,332
SURE WE CAN START OVER
IN A DIFFERENT CITY,
BUT I LOVE THIS LAND.

1136
01:08:24,334 --> 01:08:29,737
WAIT. WHY CAN'T JUST CALL
THE BANK AND ASK THEM TO WORK
SOMETHING OUT WITH US?

1137
01:08:29,739 --> 01:08:31,773
BECAUSE I AM THE BANK.

1138
01:08:33,175 --> 01:08:37,212
AND MY BOSS WON'T
BAIL YOU OUT OF DEBT.

1139
01:08:37,214 --> 01:08:43,718
THERE ARE SOME BUSINESSMEN AND
THEY HAVE MADE A VERY LARGE
OFFER FOR THE LAND-- JAKE!

1140
01:08:44,753 --> 01:08:45,753
YOU LIED TO ME.

1141
01:08:45,755 --> 01:08:46,488
I DIDN'T LIE TO YOU.

1142
01:08:46,490 --> 01:08:49,824
- I JUST DIDN'T
KNOW HOW TO TELL YOU.
- LYING AND NOT TELLING

1143
01:08:49,826 --> 01:08:52,961
ARE THE SAME THING TO ME.

1144
01:08:59,502 --> 01:09:02,270
[SOBBING]

1145
01:09:05,074 --> 01:09:08,576
JAKE, WAIT.

1146
01:09:11,647 --> 01:09:13,081
IT'S NOT HER FAULT.

1147
01:09:13,083 --> 01:09:14,549
YEAH? AND WHOSE FAULT IS IT?

1148
01:09:14,551 --> 01:09:16,117
YOU HID THIS FROM ME!
WHAT ABOUT THE COLLEGE?

1149
01:09:16,119 --> 01:09:18,553
<i>WHAT ABOUT THE VISION</i>
<i>THAT WE HAD?</i>

1150
01:09:18,555 --> 01:09:19,654
SON, I KNOW--

1151
01:09:19,656 --> 01:09:20,288
KNOW WHAT?

1152
01:09:20,290 --> 01:09:23,424
THAT WE'RE LOSING EVERYTHING
THAT WE'VE WORKED FOR AND YOU
DIDN'T HAVE ENOUGH RESPECT

1153
01:09:23,426 --> 01:09:26,594
FOR ME OR THE WORKERS
TO TELL US?

1154
01:09:43,546 --> 01:09:47,282
MEGHAN, HOW COULD YOU
DO THIS TO US?

1155
01:09:47,284 --> 01:09:49,584
GERI, IT'S NOT HER FAULT.

1156
01:09:49,586 --> 01:09:51,519
<i>SHE WAS JUST DOING HER JOB.</i>

1157
01:09:52,288 --> 01:09:53,254
EDEN, HOW DID
ALL THIS HAPPEN?

1158
01:09:53,256 --> 01:09:57,926
I TRIED EVERYTHING
I COULD TO STOP THIS.

1159
01:09:59,295 --> 01:10:02,230
BUT UH, OUR TIME IS SHORT.

1160
01:10:02,232 --> 01:10:05,133
I MEET WITH MS. DOHERTY
TOMORROW

1161
01:10:05,135 --> 01:10:07,368
TO FINALIZE
THE PAPERWORK.

1162
01:10:07,370 --> 01:10:10,171
SO, UM,

1163
01:10:10,173 --> 01:10:12,273
LET'S ENJOY THE REST
OF THE CAMP.

1164
01:10:12,275 --> 01:10:15,009
PASTOR, COULD YOU LEAD US
IN PRAYER?

1165
01:10:15,011 --> 01:10:16,844
SURE.

1166
01:10:20,549 --> 01:10:21,950
DEAR HEAVENLY FATHER,

1167
01:10:21,952 --> 01:10:24,118
WE ASK FOR YOUR GUIDANCE
AND YOUR WISDOM,

1168
01:10:24,120 --> 01:10:29,257
AND THAT YOU MAY POUR
YOUR BLESSING UPON YOUR WORK,

1169
01:10:29,259 --> 01:10:35,163
YOUR LAND, AND YOUR PEOPLE.

1170
01:10:39,034 --> 01:10:40,835
IN JESUS' NAME WE PRAY.

1171
01:10:40,837 --> 01:10:42,837
[ALL]
AMEN.

1172
01:10:42,839 --> 01:10:44,939
AMEN.

1173
01:10:49,178 --> 01:10:50,878
IT'S OKAY.

1174
01:10:50,880 --> 01:10:52,580
I'M SORRY.

1175
01:11:05,261 --> 01:11:07,962
<i>[MOTOR HUMMING]</i>

1176
01:11:30,185 --> 01:11:32,153
HEY.

1177
01:11:39,728 --> 01:11:41,396
YOU KNOW, AS LONG
AS I CAN REMEMBER,

1178
01:11:41,398 --> 01:11:44,866
THIS HAS BEEN MY SPOT TO COME
AND GET AWAY FROM THE WORLD,

1179
01:11:44,868 --> 01:11:50,972
CLEAR MY MIND FROM
ANY WORRIES, DOUBTS,

1180
01:11:50,974 --> 01:11:53,341
FEARS.

1181
01:11:54,643 --> 01:11:57,278
I'M SORRY.

1182
01:11:57,880 --> 01:12:02,483
I DIDN'T MEAN TO MISLEAD
YOU WHY I WAS HERE.

1183
01:12:03,419 --> 01:12:05,553
I'M JUST DOING MY JOB.

1184
01:12:05,555 --> 01:12:07,755
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN.
RIGHT? LIKE,

1185
01:12:07,757 --> 01:12:09,724
WHO DRIVES UP HERE
IN A FERRARI?

1186
01:12:09,726 --> 01:12:12,093
IT'S GOTTA BE
A BANKER OR A LAWYER,

1187
01:12:12,095 --> 01:12:14,162
SOMEBODY SELF-ORIENTED.

1188
01:12:14,164 --> 01:12:15,563
YEAH, THAT WOULD BE ME.

1189
01:12:15,565 --> 01:12:20,201
I WAS EXACTLY THAT PERSON
YOU JUST DESCRIBED WHEN
I CAME HERE.

1190
01:12:20,203 --> 01:12:22,003
I WAS ON A MISSION
TO CLOSE ON THIS DEAL

1191
01:12:22,005 --> 01:12:27,475
AND GET BACK IN TIME
TO HAVE DRINKS WITH
MY FRIENDS IN THE CITY.

1192
01:12:27,910 --> 01:12:31,412
BUT SOMETHING CHANGED.

1193
01:12:32,381 --> 01:12:35,116
AFTER SEEING ALL THIS,

1194
01:12:35,118 --> 01:12:37,285
AND YOU SHARING YOUR--

1195
01:12:37,287 --> 01:12:39,654
YOUR VISION WITH ME,

1196
01:12:39,656 --> 01:12:40,755
AND MEETING EVERYONE,
I UNDERSTAND WHY

1197
01:12:40,757 --> 01:12:45,493
YOUR FATHER
DOESN'T WANT TO PART
WITH THIS LAND.

1198
01:12:46,428 --> 01:12:50,331
THIS REALLY IS GOD'S COUNTRY!

1199
01:12:51,066 --> 01:12:53,534
LOOK, I KNOW I CAN'T
BLAME YOU,

1200
01:12:53,536 --> 01:12:57,171
BUT I DON'T
HAVE TO LIKE IT.

1201
01:13:17,826 --> 01:13:20,128
[CRYING]

1202
01:13:35,878 --> 01:13:39,714
I'M SORRY.
I'M SO SORRY.

1203
01:13:39,716 --> 01:13:41,716
I FEEL SO BAD.

1204
01:13:41,718 --> 01:13:46,487
DON'T. I REALIZE THAT YOU
WERE JUST DOING YOUR JOB.

1205
01:13:46,489 --> 01:13:54,162
AND THAT I NEED TO FORGIVE
LIKE JESUS WOULD HAVE.

1206
01:13:57,933 --> 01:14:00,735
DO YOU WANT
TO FORGIVE ME?

1207
01:14:00,737 --> 01:14:04,405
YES. YES, I DO.

1208
01:14:04,407 --> 01:14:05,740
I REALLY ENJOYED
WHAT WE SHARED TOGETHER.

1209
01:14:05,742 --> 01:14:11,145
AND I LEARNED THAT THERE'S A
LESSON IN EVERY PART OF LIFE

1210
01:14:11,147 --> 01:14:13,381
AND IT IS NOT YOUR FAULT
THAT THIS CAMP IS BROKE.

1211
01:14:13,383 --> 01:14:19,387
THAT'S SOMETHING THAT JAKE
AND EDEN AND CAROLINE
HAVE TO DEAL WITH.

1212
01:14:19,389 --> 01:14:23,891
SO--
I'M GONNA GO FOR A WALK.

1213
01:14:23,893 --> 01:14:27,929
WANT ME TO COME
FOR A WALK WITH YOU?

1214
01:14:28,764 --> 01:14:30,264
I'D RATHER BE BY MYSELF.

1215
01:14:30,266 --> 01:14:34,836
I JUST-- I HAVE
A LOT TO THINK ABOUT.

1216
01:14:48,851 --> 01:14:49,984
<i>[CELL PHONE RINGS]</i>

1217
01:14:49,986 --> 01:14:52,720
<i>YOU'VE REACHED MEGHAN DOHERTY.</i>
<i>PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE.</i>

1218
01:14:52,722 --> 01:14:54,455
<i>[ADAM] MEGHAN,</i>
<i>WHITAKER'S FURIOUS.</i>

1219
01:14:54,457 --> 01:14:56,457
<i>HE PLANS TO COME OUT THERE</i>
<i>IF YOU DON'T CALL IN.</i>

1220
01:14:56,459 --> 01:15:02,396
<i>YOUR JOB'S AT STAKE.</i>
<i>I HOPE YOU'RE DOING</i>
<i>THE RIGHT THING.</i>

1221
01:15:05,467 --> 01:15:10,104
<i>[MEGHAN] I SHOULD JUST CLOSE</i>
<i>THE DEAL AND WALK AWAY.</i>

1222
01:15:10,106 --> 01:15:13,274
THAT'S ALL YOU HAVE
TO DO. YOU'VE DONE IT
A MILLION TIMES BEFORE

1223
01:15:13,276 --> 01:15:17,712
AND IT'S GOTTEN YOU A FERRARI,
A HOME OUT IN THE HOLLYWOOD
HILLS,

1224
01:15:17,714 --> 01:15:19,313
I MEAN,
WHAT MORE DO YOU NEED?

1225
01:15:19,315 --> 01:15:24,285
WHO CARES IF I'VE TAKEN AWAY
EVERYTHING THAT
THEY CARE ABOUT?

1226
01:15:24,287 --> 01:15:26,454
POW!

1227
01:15:27,723 --> 01:15:31,392
WHEN HAVE I EVER
CARED BEFORE?

1228
01:15:33,195 --> 01:15:34,662
MEGHAN, JUST STAY ON TASK.

1229
01:15:34,664 --> 01:15:40,935
IT'S NOT PERSONAL. IT'S--
IT'S BUSINESS.

1230
01:15:42,838 --> 01:15:44,972
IT'S BUSINESS.

1231
01:15:51,713 --> 01:15:55,249
HEY, PASTOR TINSLEY!

1232
01:15:57,653 --> 01:15:58,419
MEGHAN.

1233
01:15:58,421 --> 01:16:01,055
HOW DO YOU FEEL TODAY?

1234
01:16:01,057 --> 01:16:03,157
CONFUSED.

1235
01:16:03,159 --> 01:16:04,892
OKAY, I'M LISTENING.

1236
01:16:04,894 --> 01:16:08,029
YESTERDAY I FELT SO BAD,
AND--

1237
01:16:08,031 --> 01:16:09,463
TODAY IS THE LAST DAY,

1238
01:16:09,465 --> 01:16:13,067
AND I JUST FEEL LIKE
THE EXECUTIONER.

1239
01:16:13,069 --> 01:16:16,537
YOU'RE A GOOD SERVANT.
THAT'S ALL GOD WANTS US
TO BE IS GOOD SERVANTS.

1240
01:16:16,539 --> 01:16:22,977
I GUESS I'VE JUST
BEEN EXPERIENCING THIS
OVERWHELMING AMOUNT OF GUILT

1241
01:16:22,979 --> 01:16:23,911
THESE LAST FEW DAYS.

1242
01:16:23,913 --> 01:16:27,715
IF IT'S GOD'S WILL,
THEN IT'S HIS WILL.

1243
01:16:27,717 --> 01:16:28,816
YOU'RE ONLY HIS MESSENGER.

1244
01:16:28,818 --> 01:16:31,686
I JUST FEEL LIKE THERE'S
SOMETHING THAT I SHOULD DO.

1245
01:16:31,688 --> 01:16:35,056
IF THIS IS GOD'S WILL
THEN IT'S HIS WILL.

1246
01:16:40,562 --> 01:16:42,997
GOOD LUCK.

1247
01:16:45,467 --> 01:16:47,168
EVERYBODY READY?

1248
01:17:14,062 --> 01:17:18,499
HEY! JAKE! JAKE! JAKE!

1249
01:17:18,501 --> 01:17:22,069
JAKE, LISTEN. GRAB
YOUR TRUCK AND COME WITH ME.

1250
01:17:22,071 --> 01:17:22,737
WHAT'S GOING ON?

1251
01:17:22,739 --> 01:17:26,307
I DON'T HAVE TIME TO EXPLAIN.
JUST FOLLOW ME.

1252
01:17:26,408 --> 01:17:28,843
LISTEN, JAKE,
I KNOW YOU DON; T TRUST ME,
BUT I HAVE AN IDEA.

1253
01:17:28,845 --> 01:17:30,845
I'VE HAD ENOUGH
OF YOUR IDEAS, OKAY?
WHY SHOULD I TRUST YOU?

1254
01:17:30,847 --> 01:17:34,682
YOU STANDING HERE MAD AT ME
IS NOT GOING TO
SAVE THIS LAND.

1255
01:17:34,684 --> 01:17:38,686
LET'S GO TO YOUR ROOM.
GET YOUR BUSINESS PLAN.

1256
01:17:38,688 --> 01:17:40,855
I HAVE AN IDEA.

1257
01:17:40,857 --> 01:17:45,426
IF YOU DON'T TRUST ME,
THEN TRUST GOD.

1258
01:17:47,462 --> 01:17:48,562
COME ON.

1259
01:17:48,564 --> 01:17:51,866
COME ON! COME ON! COME ON!

1260
01:18:09,518 --> 01:18:11,419
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

1261
01:18:11,421 --> 01:18:14,889
MEGHAN, OH MY GOD!
WHERE ARE YOU? WE'VE
BEEN WORRIED SICK!

1262
01:18:14,891 --> 01:18:18,125
<i>ADAM, I'M FINE.</i>
<i>TELL WHITAKER NOTHING, OKAY?</i>

1263
01:18:18,127 --> 01:18:18,959
I CAN'T JUST DO THAT.

1264
01:18:18,961 --> 01:18:21,996
LOOK, YOU FELL OFF
THE FACE OF THE EARTH.
WE ALL HAVE QUESTIONS.

1265
01:18:21,998 --> 01:18:25,266
<i>CALL JASON AND TELL HIM THAT</i>
<i>I AM ON MY WAY BEARING GIFTS.</i>

1266
01:18:25,268 --> 01:18:27,234
<i>OKAY, MY FRIEND?</i>

1267
01:18:27,236 --> 01:18:29,670
YEAH, OKAY.

1268
01:18:32,207 --> 01:18:33,741
MY CAR.
TAKE IT. IT'S YOURS.

1269
01:18:33,743 --> 01:18:38,412
JASON, YOU TOLD ME IF
I HAD A GREAT OPPORTUNITY,
YOU WANTED IN.

1270
01:18:38,414 --> 01:18:40,748
WHAT IS IT?
THIS IS IT.

1271
01:18:40,750 --> 01:18:42,683
IT'S THE FUTURE.

1272
01:18:42,685 --> 01:18:45,820
I HOPE YOU HAVE
YOUR CHECK BOOK.

1273
01:18:47,522 --> 01:18:49,957
<i>[CELL PHONE RINGS]</i>

1274
01:18:53,895 --> 01:18:54,595
HELLO.

1275
01:18:54,597 --> 01:18:56,530
<i>[HOSHI YAKAMOTO]</i>
<i>MR. WHITAKER, WE CAN NO</i>
<i>LONGER WAIT.</i>

1276
01:18:56,532 --> 01:18:59,867
<i>I THOUGHT YOU SAID THE DEAL</i>
<i>WOULD BE CLOSED BY TODAY.</i>

1277
01:18:59,869 --> 01:19:01,268
HOSHI, RELAX.

1278
01:19:01,270 --> 01:19:04,605
I GAVE YOU MY WORD. YOU
KNOW HOW THESE LAWYERS WORK,

1279
01:19:04,607 --> 01:19:07,308
GOING OVER ALL THAT PAPERWORK.
IT TAKES SOME TIME.

1280
01:19:07,310 --> 01:19:09,844
<i>I UNDERSTAND THAT,</i>
<i>MR. WHITAKER.</i>

1281
01:19:09,846 --> 01:19:11,512
<i>BUT WE HAD A DEAL.</i>

1282
01:19:11,514 --> 01:19:13,881
<i>AND WE AGREED UPON A DEADLINE.</i>

1283
01:19:13,883 --> 01:19:15,149
YEAH, BUT--

1284
01:19:15,151 --> 01:19:17,051
<i>I'LL WAIT FOR YOUR CALL.</i>

1285
01:19:25,327 --> 01:19:28,362
[MURMURING]

1286
01:19:28,364 --> 01:19:29,964
ALL RIGHT, GATHER AROUND,
FOLKS.

1287
01:19:29,966 --> 01:19:31,766
<i>WE'RE GONNA START THE AUCTION</i>
<i>IN ABOUT FIVE MINUTES.</i>

1288
01:19:31,768 --> 01:19:37,705
<i>NOW, WHAT YOU'RE GONNA BE</i>
<i>BIDDING ON IS 1,000 ACRES</i>
<i>OF GOD'S COUNTRY.</i>

1289
01:19:37,707 --> 01:19:43,310
PLEASE, SERIOUS BIDDERS ONLY.
INCLUDES THREE NICE TRAILERS,

1290
01:19:43,312 --> 01:19:46,914
LOVELY LITTLE LOG CABIN,
AND A PRIVATE LAKE.

1291
01:19:46,916 --> 01:19:52,887
ALL RIGHT, WE'LL START
THE BIDDING AT 75,000.

1292
01:19:52,889 --> 01:19:55,856
[TRUCK SCREECHES]

1293
01:19:55,858 --> 01:19:56,791
WAIT!

1294
01:19:56,793 --> 01:19:58,826
- 1,000 ACRES OF--
- NO NO NO NO! WAIT WAIT
WAIT WAIT!

1295
01:19:58,828 --> 01:20:02,396
I GOT IT. I GOT THE PAYMENT.
HERE YOU GO.

1296
01:20:02,398 --> 01:20:07,101
I'M WITH
WHITAKER AND ASSOCIATES
AND I HEREBY PRESENT TO YOU

1297
01:20:07,103 --> 01:20:10,905
TO RESTORE THE LAND
INTO GOOD STANDING.

1298
01:20:11,773 --> 01:20:13,107
EVERYTHING SEEMS
TO BE IN ORDER.

1299
01:20:13,109 --> 01:20:17,945
SORRY, FOLKS,
NO AUCTION TODAY.

1300
01:20:21,850 --> 01:20:23,617
THANKS.

1301
01:20:25,754 --> 01:20:33,427
MEGHAN, I HOPE THAT SMILE IS
BECAUSE
WHITAKER AND ASSOCIATES

1302
01:20:36,998 --> 01:20:38,766
NO.

1303
01:20:39,034 --> 01:20:41,101
WE HAVE A NEW PARTNER.

1304
01:20:41,403 --> 01:20:42,603
GOD'S COUNTRY'S GONNA SURVIVE,

1305
01:20:42,605 --> 01:20:45,639
SO WE CAN CONTINUE TO
SAVE LIVES AND GIVE BACK.

1306
01:20:45,641 --> 01:20:49,143
DO YOU THINK THE WORLD NEEDS
ANOTHER CASINO
TO TAKE PEOPLE'S

1307
01:20:49,145 --> 01:20:52,279
WHY COULDN'T YOU
BUILD SOMETHING
THAT GIVES BACK TO MANKIND?

1308
01:20:52,281 --> 01:20:55,583
MEGHAN, YOU GOTTA
BE KIDDING ME.

1309
01:20:55,585 --> 01:20:57,084
NO, I'M NOT, SIR.

1310
01:20:57,086 --> 01:21:01,055
<i>AFTER SPENDING TIME HERE</i>
<i>AND SEEING WHAT THIS LAND</i>
<i>WAS REALLY ABOUT,</i>

1311
01:21:01,057 --> 01:21:05,526
I REALIZED I COULD NOT BE
A PART OF BUILDING A CASINO
OUT HERE.

1312
01:21:05,528 --> 01:21:07,828
THERE ARE SO MANY OTHER PIECES
OF LAND IN THIS VAST DESERT

1313
01:21:07,830 --> 01:21:11,165
WHERE
THE YAKAMOTO BROTHERS CAN
BUILD THEIR CASINO ON.

1314
01:21:11,167 --> 01:21:15,436
THIS LITTLE
PIECE OF LAND, THIS
IS TOO VALUABLE,

1315
01:21:15,438 --> 01:21:18,405
TO THIS CAMP,
TO THESE PEOPLE,

1316
01:21:18,407 --> 01:21:22,209
AND NOW ME.

1317
01:21:25,247 --> 01:21:29,550
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE FIRED.

1318
01:21:29,552 --> 01:21:31,518
I KNOW.

1319
01:21:31,520 --> 01:21:33,120
MEGHAN, I TRUSTED YOU

1320
01:21:33,122 --> 01:21:37,391
TO COME UP HERE
AND DO THE RIGHT THING!

1321
01:21:37,393 --> 01:21:39,126
AND YOU CROSSED ME?

1322
01:21:39,128 --> 01:21:40,194
I DID DO THE RIGHT THING,

1323
01:21:40,196 --> 01:21:45,232
AND IT TOOK BEING UP HERE
AT GOD'S COUNTRY AND THIS LAND
TO FINALLY REALIZE THAT.

1324
01:21:45,234 --> 01:21:51,205
NOW IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
WE HAVE A COLLEGE TO BUILD.

1325
01:22:02,684 --> 01:22:04,718
[MEGHAN LAUGHS]

1326
01:22:11,826 --> 01:22:16,196
MAN, I CAN NOT
BELIEVE YOU GOT RID
OF THAT SWEET RIDE.

1327
01:22:16,198 --> 01:22:18,766
LISTEN, I'M GONNA BE IN LOS
ANGELES IN A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

1328
01:22:18,768 --> 01:22:22,836
MAYBE I CAN COME DOWN
THERE AND WE CAN HANG OUT.

1329
01:22:22,838 --> 01:22:24,305
PROMISE.

1330
01:22:24,307 --> 01:22:26,140
YES.

1331
01:22:30,211 --> 01:22:31,745
OH, STOP IT.

1332
01:22:31,747 --> 01:22:33,881
I'M GONNA GO GET THE TRUCK.

1333
01:22:33,883 --> 01:22:35,482
ALL RIGHT.

1334
01:22:35,484 --> 01:22:38,052
I'M REALLY GONNA MISS YOU.

1335
01:22:38,054 --> 01:22:40,220
I TOLD YOU I WANT YOU
TO COME HANG OUT WITH ME.

1336
01:22:40,222 --> 01:22:43,123
YEAH, BUT YOU'RE
JUST SAYING THAT NOW.

1337
01:22:43,125 --> 01:22:44,224
PROMISE.

1338
01:22:44,226 --> 01:22:46,660
YOU'RE SPECIAL.

1339
01:22:47,529 --> 01:22:49,596
THANK YOU.

1340
01:22:50,632 --> 01:22:54,668
MEGHAN, WE'RE TRULY
GONNA MISS YOU.

1341
01:22:55,437 --> 01:22:57,338
HOW DID YOU KNOW?

1342
01:22:57,340 --> 01:23:00,607
I DIDN'T. HE DID.

1343
01:23:07,282 --> 01:23:08,615
YOU READY TO GO?

1344
01:23:08,617 --> 01:23:11,285
I AM.

1345
01:23:17,759 --> 01:23:22,663
SO, PARTNER, YOU READY
TO TAKE ME BACK TO THE HUSTLE
AND BUSTLE OF CITY LIFE?

1346
01:23:22,665 --> 01:23:24,465
YOU KNOW YOU'RE ALWAYS
WELCOME TO STAY HERE.

1347
01:23:24,467 --> 01:23:26,133
YOU CAN TEACH BUSINESS
FINANCE AT THE COLLEGE.

1348
01:23:26,135 --> 01:23:30,404
TRUST ME. I'LL BE BACK
TO CHECK ON MY NEW VENTURE.

1349
01:23:30,406 --> 01:23:32,840
ESPECIALLY SINCE
I'M OFFICIALLY UNEMPLOYED.

1350
01:23:32,842 --> 01:23:39,079
YEAH, WELL, I HOPE BUSINESS
ISN'T THE ONLY REASON
YOU COME BACK.

1351
01:23:39,081 --> 01:23:43,751
- HOW ABOUT I BUY YOU DINNER?
- [MEGHAN] YOU KNOW, I KNOW
A GREAT SUSHI PLACE.

1352
01:23:43,753 --> 01:23:47,321
[MEGHAN] HEY, DO YOU HAVE
ANY PLANS TOMORROW?

1353
01:23:47,323 --> 01:23:50,224
WHY? WHAT DO YOU
HAVE IN MIND?

1354
01:23:57,232 --> 01:23:59,800
[PHONE RINGS]

1355
01:23:59,802 --> 01:24:03,370
HELLO? MEGHAN!

1356
01:24:06,975 --> 01:24:07,508
OH.

1357
01:24:07,510 --> 01:24:11,712
WELL, I CAN'T SAY
I'M NOT DISAPPOINTED.

1358
01:24:12,213 --> 01:24:14,481
WELL, I KNOW THAT YOU'RE BUSY.

1359
01:24:14,483 --> 01:24:15,315
<i>[DOORBELL RINGS]</i>

1360
01:24:15,317 --> 01:24:21,555
MEGHAN, CAN YOU WAIT A SECOND?
THERE'S SOMEONE AT THE DOOR.

1361
01:24:21,557 --> 01:24:23,424
BE RIGHT BACK.

1362
01:24:25,226 --> 01:24:27,528
<i>[DOORBELL RINGS]</i>

1363
01:24:29,264 --> 01:24:31,298
OH!

1364
01:24:32,434 --> 01:24:33,200
YES?

1365
01:24:33,202 --> 01:24:36,437
HI. I HAVE A DELIVERY
FOR A MS. EMMA DOHERTY.

1366
01:24:36,439 --> 01:24:37,337
THAT'S ME.

1367
01:24:37,339 --> 01:24:38,806
GREAT. THESE ARE FOR YOU.

1368
01:24:38,808 --> 01:24:40,007
OH, THANK YOU.

1369
01:24:40,009 --> 01:24:41,442
HAVE A GREAT DAY.

1370
01:24:41,444 --> 01:24:43,043
BYE.
YOU TOO.

1371
01:24:46,081 --> 01:24:48,715
OH, MEGHAN.

1372
01:24:52,387 --> 01:24:52,953
OKAY, I'M BACK.

1373
01:24:52,955 --> 01:24:56,623
I JUST RECEIVED THE FLOWERS.
HOW BEAUTIFUL! THANK YOU.

1374
01:24:56,625 --> 01:24:59,493
AT LEAST YOU DIDN'T
FORGET ABOUT ME.

1375
01:24:59,495 --> 01:25:00,561
<i>[DOORBELL RINGS]</i>

1376
01:25:00,563 --> 01:25:03,597
AGAIN? PLEASE HOLD.

1377
01:25:08,903 --> 01:25:10,003
OH!

1378
01:25:10,005 --> 01:25:11,105
SURPRISE!

1379
01:25:11,107 --> 01:25:15,175
OH, MY GOD! MEGHAN!

1380
01:25:15,443 --> 01:25:17,211
OH, SWEETHEART!

1381
01:25:17,213 --> 01:25:19,546
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, MOM.

1382
01:25:19,548 --> 01:25:23,183
OH! THANK YOU.
COME IN.

1383
01:25:23,185 --> 01:25:23,984
OH MY GOD!

1384
01:25:23,986 --> 01:25:28,088
- HAPPY BIRTHDAY!
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.
- THANK YOU!

1385
01:25:28,090 --> 01:25:29,957
THIS IS JAKE.

1386
01:25:29,959 --> 01:25:31,892
HI, I'M JAKE.

1387
01:25:31,894 --> 01:25:33,093
HI!

1388
01:25:33,095 --> 01:25:34,528
YEAH, I KNOW!

1389
01:25:34,530 --> 01:25:35,262
COME IN!

1390
01:25:35,264 --> 01:25:41,435
OH, SWEETHEART,
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU DID THIS!

1391
01:25:41,437 --> 01:25:42,903
HEY, COME ON!

1392
01:25:42,905 --> 01:25:47,141
I WAS SO SURPRISED!
I JUST COULDN'T BELIEVE IT.

1393
01:25:47,143 --> 01:25:48,408
I ACTUALLY GOT YOU
A LITTLE SOMETHING.

1394
01:25:48,410 --> 01:25:50,644
JAKE, THANK YOU.
THAT'S VERY SWEET OF YOU.

1395
01:25:50,646 --> 01:25:54,114
YOU'RE VERY WELCOME.
YOUR DAUGHTER'S VERY
IMPORTANT TO ME

1396
01:25:54,116 --> 01:25:56,517
IN THE LITTLE TIME
I'VE KNOWN HER.

1397
01:25:56,519 --> 01:25:58,585
THAT'S SO SWEET. THANK YOU.

1398
01:25:58,587 --> 01:26:03,157
[MURMURING]

1399
01:26:03,159 --> 01:26:06,126
YAY! CAKE!

1400
01:26:07,495 --> 01:26:10,330
OH, LOOK AT THAT!

1401
01:26:11,065 --> 01:26:14,601
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, MOM.

1402
01:26:14,603 --> 01:26:16,136
YOU THINK IT'S BIG ENOUGH?

1403
01:26:16,138 --> 01:26:17,471
[ALL LAUGH]

1404
01:26:17,473 --> 01:26:20,440
I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

1405
01:26:20,442 --> 01:26:22,342
OH!

1406
01:26:22,344 --> 01:26:26,313
HEY, YOU MEAN
THE WORLD TO ME.

1407
01:26:29,217 --> 01:26:30,717
THANKS, SWEETIE.

1408
01:26:31,352 --> 01:26:34,388
OKAY, NOW BLOW OUT
YOUR CANDLES.

1409
01:26:34,390 --> 01:26:37,424
OKAY. READY?

1410
01:26:44,032 --> 01:26:46,667
<i>[MUSIC PLAYS]</i>

1411
01:30:47,508 --> 01:30:50,310
<i>[MUSIC ENDS]</i>

